{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841750240,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786800c1001xla6V21h6qIqqU","messageID":"msg_d7867e2a6001puRrNlf200Ew2N","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_b76fd2ac4b1c4296932e3580","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore project structure","prompt":"Explore the project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to understand:\n1. What files exist (especially any existing design.md, docs/, pkg/picod/)\n2. Look for any existing Go code in pkg/ directory\n3. Check for any existing API definitions or specs\n4. Look at the overall project structure\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of what you find, including file paths and their purposes.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28797e92dffeLNXcA9a12SCmRq (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the project. Here is the comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary: AgentCube\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`  \n**Language:** Go 1.25.0  \n**Purpose:** A Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n---\n\n### 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md              # SDD (Spec-Driven Development) prompt template\n├── go.mod / go.sum             # Go module definition (github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube)\n├── coverage.out                # Test coverage output\n├── project.md                  # Project context overview\n├── proposal.md                 # AR-011: Router JWT authentication proposal\n├── design.md                   # AR-012: Session Store Interface design (detailed)\n├── delta-spec.md               # AR-016: PicoD file management API delta spec\n├── test_spec.md                # Test specification\n│\n├── cmd/                        # Binary entry points\n│   └── picod/main.go           # PicoD daemon entry point\n│\n├── pkg/                        # Go packages (core library code)\n│   ├── picod/                  # PicoD in-sandbox daemon\n│   ├── router/                 # HTTP reverse proxy / session router\n│   ├── store/                  # Session storage abstraction (Redis/Valkey)\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/  # Kubernetes CRD type definitions\n│   ├── workloadmanager/        # Sandbox lifecycle management\n│   │   ├── handler/            # HTTP handlers for sandbox CRUD\n│   │   ├── reconciler/         # K8s reconciliation logic\n│   │   └── response/           # Response helpers\n│   └── common/types/           # Shared type aliases\n│\n├── client-go/                  # Generated Kubernetes client library\n│   ├── clientset/              # Typed clientset for AgentCube CRDs\n│   ├── informers/              # Informer factories\n│   └── listers/                # Listers\n│\n├── changes/                    # Change request folders (AR-001 through AR-016)\n│   └── AR-NNN/                 # Each contains: design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md, (optional) delta-spec.md\n│\n├── code-execution/             # Code execution subsystem (design.md, spec.md)\n├── cli-toolkit/                # CLI toolkit (design.md, spec.md)\n├── ci-cd/                      # CI/CD pipeline (design.md, spec.md)\n├── deployment/                 # Deployment design (design.md, spec.md, client-go.md)\n├── idle-cleanup/               # Idle sandbox cleanup (design.md, spec.md)\n├── integrations/               # Dify plugin + PCAP analyzer (design.md, spec.md)\n├── python-sdk/                 # Python SDK (design.md, spec.md)\n├── sandbox-orchestration/      # Sandbox orchestration (design.md, spec.md)\n├── session-routing/            # Session routing (design.md, spec.md)\n├── session-store/              # Session store (design.md, spec.md)\n│\n└── testing/\n    └── agentcube_tdd_manifest.md  # TDD test contract for all core modules\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Design Documents and Specs\n\n**Root-level design/spec files:**\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` | AR-012: Session Store Interface -- detailed 687-line design for `pkg/store` with Redis/Valkey backends |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` | AR-016: PicoD file management API delta spec -- 870 lines defining 11 new file management endpoints |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md` | AR-011: Router JWT authentication and signing proposal |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` | Project context, architecture diagram, tech stack |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md` | Test specification |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | TDD manifest with test cases for WorkloadManager, Router, Store, PicoD, SDK, CLI |\n\n**Per-subsystem design/spec pairs:**\n| Subsystem | design.md | spec.md |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| `code-execution/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `ci-cd/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `deployment/` | Yes | Yes (+ `client-go.md`) |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `integrations/` | Yes | Yes (Dify plugin + PCAP analyzer) |\n| `python-sdk/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `session-routing/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `session-store/` | Yes | Yes |\n\n**Change Request (AR) folders:** AR-001 through AR-016, each containing `design.md`, `proposal.md`, `tasks.md`, and some with `delta-spec.md`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Go Code in `pkg/` Directory\n\n#### 3.1 `pkg/picod/` -- PicoD In-Sandbox Daemon (7 files + 6 test files)\n\nPicoD is a lightweight HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods, providing code execution and file management APIs protected by JWT authentication.\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go` | Gin-based HTTP server with routes: `POST /api/execute`, `POST /api/files`, `GET /api/files`, `GET /api/files/*path`, `GET /health` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/config.go` | CLI flag parsing (`--port`, `--workspace`) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/types.go` | Request/Response structs: `ExecuteRequest`, `ExecuteResponse`, `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth.go` | `AuthManager` -- RSA RS256 JWT verification middleware, public key loaded from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/execute.go` | `ExecuteHandler` -- runs commands with timeout, captures stdout/stderr/exit code |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files.go` | File operations: upload (multipart + JSON Base64), list, download, with path sanitization (workspace jail) |\n\nTest files: `server_test.go`, `config_test.go`, `auth_test.go`, `execute_test.go`, `sanitize_test.go`, `health_test.go`\n\n#### 3.2 `pkg/router/` -- HTTP Reverse Proxy / Session Router (12 files + test files)\n\nThe Router is the entry point for client traffic, performing JWT authentication, session management, and proxying requests to sandbox pods.\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/server.go` | Main server with Gin routes: `/health/live`, `/health/ready`, `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`, `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/router.go` | Low-level `Router` interface with route table and load balancer |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/config.go` | Server configuration |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware.go` | Middleware (AuthMiddleware, ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager for RS256 signing and validation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/proxy.go` | Reverse proxy logic with JWT token injection |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go` | Session management |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/backend.go` | Backend definition |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/loadbalancer.go` | Load balancer |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/health.go` | Health check handlers |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/informer.go` | K8s informer integration |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/errors.go` | Error definitions |\n\n#### 3.3 `pkg/store/` -- Session Storage Abstraction (7 files + test files)\n\nPluggable session storage supporting Redis and Valkey backends.\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store.go` | `Store` interface with methods: StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, GetSandbox, ListSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, Ping, Close |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/singleton.go` | `sync.Once` singleton pattern, provider selection via `STORE_TYPE` env var |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation (go-redis/v9) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation (valkey-io/valkey-go) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/codec.go` | Serialization codec |\n\n#### 3.4 `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` -- Kubernetes CRD Type Definitions (12 files)\n\nDefines the Custom Resource Definitions for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` | `AgentRuntime` CRD -- defines agent runtime with pod template, target ports, session timeout |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | `CodeInterpreter` CRD -- defines code interpreter with warm pool, auth mode, sandbox template |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | Shared types: `ProtocolType` (HTTP/HTTPS), `AuthModeType` (picod/none), `TargetPort` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` | Group/version registration, SchemeBuilder |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants.go` | Constants |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated deep copy methods |\n\n#### 3.5 `pkg/workloadmanager/` -- Sandbox Lifecycle Management\n\n| Sub-package | Files | Purpose |\n|-------------|-------|---------|\n| `handler/` | `sandbox_lifecycle.go`, `sandbox_create.go`, `sandbox_delete.go`, `models.go`, `constants.go` | HTTP handlers for sandbox CRUD, lifecycle management (GC, TTL, idle cleanup), request/response models |\n| `reconciler/` | `reconciler.go`, `agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`, `pod.go`, `sync.go`, `event_handlers.go`, `types.go`, `metrics.go` | K8s controller reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs |\n| `response/` | `response.go` | HTTP response helpers |\n\n#### 3.6 `pkg/common/types/` -- Shared Type Aliases\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/common/types/types.go` | Type aliases: `SandboxInfo` and `EntryPoint` (re-exported from `pkg/workloadmanager/handler`), kind constants |\n\n---\n\n### 4. API Definitions / Specs\n\n**No `.proto` files, OpenAPI YAML, or JSON API specs exist.** API definitions are expressed through:\n\n1. **Go struct types** with JSON tags (the primary API contract):\n   - `pkg/picod/types.go` -- PicoD API types\n   - `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` -- WorkloadManager API types\n   - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/*.go` -- Kubernetes CRD types\n\n2. **Markdown spec documents** with Gherkin-style scenarios:\n   - `delta-spec.md` (AR-016) -- 870 lines of detailed file management API spec\n   - `integrations/spec.md` -- Dify plugin and PCAP analyzer specs\n   - Per-subsystem `spec.md` files in each subsystem folder\n\n3. **Change request documents** in `changes/AR-NNN/` folders containing design, proposal, and task breakdowns.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Architecture Summary\n\n```\nClient / SDK / CLI\n  --> Router (Deployment :8080)\n       - JWT Auth (RS256)\n       - Session-aware routing\n       - Concurrency limiting\n       - Proxies to sandbox pods\n       <---> Redis/Valkey (session store)\n       --> WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n            - Sandbox CRUD API\n            - GC lifecycle management (TTL + idle cleanup)\n            - K8s CRD reconciliation\n            <---> Redis/Valkey\n            --> K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n  Sandbox Pods (with PicoD daemon)\n       - POST /api/execute (run commands)\n       - POST /api/files (upload)\n       - GET /api/files (list)\n       - GET /api/files/*path (download)\n       - GET /health\n       - JWT auth via PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n  Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n  Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Key Dependencies (from go.mod)\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT RS256 authentication |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n| `k8s.io/api`, `k8s.io/apimachinery`, `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes API |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | K8s controller framework |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Metrics |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | In-memory Redis for testing |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | UUID generation |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28797e92dffeLNXcA9a12SCmRq","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore project structure","time":{"start":1775841580751,"end":1775841750237}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775841750295,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786aace00014ISL2JsUwADqc0","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7867e2a6001puRrNlf200Ew2N","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19607,"input":19256,"output":175,"reasoning":176,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.005894157}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775841752668,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786ab659001yCjlyaKjl54jmn","messageID":"msg_d786aad2b001moFrHKB7LouY1F","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841754840,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786ababe001ccYt615PFcg5uQ","messageID":"msg_d786aad2b001moFrHKB7LouY1F","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6f40ce8df6ed4c4b8b8df209","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016: PicoD 文件管理 API — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `pkg/picod`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `code-execution/spec.md`, `delta-spec.md` (AR-015), `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Route table reorganization\n13: \n14: The system SHALL reorganize file management routes under explicit sub-paths. The following routes SHALL exist under the `/api` group with JWT auth middleware:\n15: \n16: | Method | Path | Handler |\n17: |--------|------|---------|\n18: | POST | `/api/files/read` | ReadFileHandler |\n19: | POST | `/api/files/write` | WriteFileHandler |\n20: | GET | `/api/files/stat` | StatFileHandler |\n21: | GET | `/api/files` | ListFilesHandler |\n22: | POST | `/api/files/upload` | UploadFileHandler |\n23: | GET | `/api/files/download` | DownloadFileHandler |\n24: | POST | `/api/files/delete` | DeleteFileHandler |\n25: | POST | `/api/files/move` | MoveFileHandler |\n26: | POST | `/api/files/mkdir` | MkDirHandler |\n27: | POST | `/api/files/search` | SearchFilesHandler |\n28: | POST | `/api/files/chmod` | ChmodHandler |\n29: \n30: The legacy routes `POST /api/files` (upload), `GET /api/files` (list), and `GET /api/files/*path` (download) from AR-015 SHALL be replaced. `GET /api/files` SHALL serve dual purpose: with `path` query parameter it lists directory contents; without `path` it returns HTTP 400.\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: All new routes are registered\n33: \n34: - **GIVEN** `NewServer` completes successfully\n35: - **WHEN** the route table is inspected\n36: - **THEN** all eleven file management routes exist under `/api/files/*` plus `POST /api/execute` and `GET /health`\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: Legacy POST /api/files upload route is removed\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** the AR-016 server is running\n41: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /api/files` with multipart content\n42: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 (route no longer exists) or HTTP 400 (no `path` query parameter)\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Legacy GET /api/files/*path download route is removed\n45: \n46: - **GIVEN** the AR-016 server is running\n47: - **WHEN** a client calls `GET /api/files/some/file.txt`\n48: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 (wildcard route no longer exists)\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Download uses query parameter\n51: \n52: - **GIVEN** a file exists at `workspaceDir/docs/readme.md`\n53: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/download?path=docs/readme.md`\n54: - **THEN** the file is served with appropriate download headers\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Config extension for file management\n57: \n58: The `Config` struct SHALL be extended with the following fields:\n59: \n60: | Field | Type | Default | Meaning |\n61: |-------|------|---------|---------|\n62: | `MaxChunkSize` | `int64` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | Maximum size per chunk in chunked transfer |\n63: | `MaxBatchSize` | `int` | `100` | Maximum number of paths in a single batch operation |\n64: | `MaxSearchResults` | `int` | `100` | Maximum number of results returned by search |\n65: | `MaxSearchDepth` | `int` | `50` | Maximum directory depth for glob search |\n66: \n67: The CLI flag parser SHALL accept `--max-chunk-size`, `--max-batch-size`, `--max-search-results`, and `--max-search-depth`.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Default config values\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** no file management flags are provided\n72: - **WHEN** `ParseFlags` returns\n73: - **THEN** `MaxChunkSize` is `33554432`, `MaxBatchSize` is `100`, `MaxSearchResults` is `100`, `MaxSearchDepth` is `50`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Custom config values\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** `--max-chunk-size=16777216 --max-batch-size=50 --max-search-results=200 --max-search-depth=20`\n78: - **WHEN** `ParseFlags` returns\n79: - **THEN** the config fields reflect the provided values\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: ReadFile API\n82: \n83: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files/read` with JSON body binding to `ReadFileRequest`. The handler SHALL read file content from the sanitized path, encode as Base64, and return `ReadFileResponse`.\n84: \n85: ```\n86: ReadFileRequest:\n87:   path:   string (required)\n88:   offset: int64  (optional, default: 0)\n89:   limit:  int64  (optional, default: -1 meaning read to EOF)\n90: \n91: ReadFileResponse:\n92:   content:    string (Base64 encoded)\n93:   total_size: int64  (full file size)\n94:   read_bytes: int64  (actual bytes read)\n95: ```\n96: \n97: The handler SHALL open the file, seek to `offset`, read up to `limit` bytes (or to EOF if `limit < 0`), and Base64-encode the result. If `offset` exceeds file size, `content` SHALL be empty and `read_bytes` SHALL be `0`.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Read entire file\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** a file `workspaceDir/hello.txt` containing `\"Hello, World!\"` (13 bytes)\n102: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/files/read` with `{\"path\": \"hello.txt\"}`\n103: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 200 with `{\"content\": \"<base64 of 'Hello, World!'>\", \"total_size\": 13, \"read_bytes\": 13}`\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Read with offset\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** a file containing `\"Hello, World!\"`\n108: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"hello.txt\", \"offset\": 7}`\n109: - **THEN** `content` is Base64 of `\"World!\"`, `total_size` is `13`, `read_bytes` is `6`\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Read with offset and limit\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** a file containing `\"Hello, World!\"`\n114: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"hello.txt\", \"offset\": 7, \"limit\": 5}`\n115: - **THEN** `content` is Base64 of `\"World\"`, `total_size` is `13`, `read_bytes` is `5`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Offset exceeds file size\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** a file containing `\"Hi\"` (2 bytes)\n120: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"hi.txt\", \"offset\": 100}`\n121: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 200 with `{\"content\": \"\", \"total_size\": 2, \"read_bytes\": 0}`\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Limit exceeds remaining bytes\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** a file containing `\"Hello\"` (5 bytes)\n126: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"hello.txt\", \"offset\": 3, \"limit\": 100}`\n127: - **THEN** `content` is Base64 of `\"lo\"`, `total_size` is `5`, `read_bytes` is `2`\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Read directory returns error\n130: \n131: - **GIVEN** `path` points to a directory\n132: - **WHEN** the handler attempts to read\n133: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `{\"error\": \"Path is a directory, not a file\", \"code\": 400}`\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: File not found\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** `path` does not exist\n138: - **WHEN** the handler attempts to open the file\n139: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"File not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Path traversal blocked\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `path` is `\"../../etc/passwd\"`\n144: - **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n145: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with access denied error\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Negative offset treated as zero\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** a file containing `\"test\"`\n150: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"offset\": -1}`\n151: - **THEN** the handler treats offset as `0` and reads the entire file\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: WriteFile API\n154: \n155: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files/write` with JSON body binding to `WriteFileRequest`. The handler SHALL decode Base64 content and write to the sanitized path.\n156: \n157: ```\n158: WriteFileRequest:\n159:   path:          string (required)\n160:   content:       string (Base64 encoded, required)\n161:   offset:        int64  (optional, default: 0)\n162:   mode:          string (optional, \"overwrite\" | \"append\", default: \"overwrite\")\n163:   create_parent: bool   (optional, default: false)\n164: ```\n165: \n166: In `overwrite` mode with `offset=0`, the file SHALL be truncated and replaced. In `overwrite` mode with `offset>0`, the handler SHALL seek to offset and overwrite bytes in place without truncating beyond the written data. In `append` mode, the content SHALL be appended to the end of the file (offset is ignored). If `create_parent` is true, parent directories SHALL be created with mode `0755`.\n167: \n168: ```\n169: WriteFileResponse:\n170:   path:        string (relative to workspace)\n171:   size:        int64  (new file size after write)\n172:   bytes_written: int64\n173: ```\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Overwrite entire file\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** a file `workspaceDir/data.txt` containing `\"old content\"`\n178: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/files/write` with `{\"path\": \"data.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of 'new content'>\"}`\n179: - **THEN** the file contains `\"new content\"`, and the response is HTTP 200 with `{\"path\": \"data.txt\", \"size\": 11, \"bytes_written\": 11}`\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Append to file\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** a file containing `\"Hello\"`\n184: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"hello.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of ', World!'>\", \"mode\": \"append\"}`\n185: - **THEN** the file contains `\"Hello, World!\"`, and `bytes_written` is `8`\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Write at offset\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** a file containing `\"Hello, World!\"` (13 bytes)\n190: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"hello.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of 'GO'>\", \"offset\": 7}`\n191: - **THEN** the file contains `\"Hello, GOrld!\"`, and `bytes_written` is `2`\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Create parent directories\n194: \n195: - **GIVEN** directory `workspaceDir/a/` exists but `a/b/` does not\n196: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"a/b/c.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of 'data'>\", \"create_parent\": true}`\n197: - **THEN** directories `a/b/` are created with mode `0755`, file `c.txt` is written, and response is HTTP 200\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Create parent disabled fails\n200: \n201: - **GIVEN** parent directory does not exist\n202: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"nonexistent/dir/file.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of 'data'>\", \"create_parent\": false}`\n203: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 or 500 with an error describing the failure to create the file\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Invalid Base64 content\n206: \n207: - **GIVEN** `\"content\": \"not-valid-base64!!!\"`\n208: - **WHEN** `base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString` is called\n209: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON error describing invalid base64\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Write to directory returns error\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** `path` points to a directory\n214: - **WHEN** the handler attempts to write\n215: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with error indicating path is a directory\n216: \n217: ### Requirement: StatFile API\n218: \n219: The system SHALL accept `GET /api/files/stat?path=...` and return metadata about the file or directory at the sanitized path.\n220: \n221: ```\n222: StatFileResponse:\n223:   name:       string\n224:   size:       int64\n225:   mode:       string (octal permission string, e.g. \"0755\")\n226:   mod_time:   time.Time\n227:   is_dir:     bool\n228:   is_symlink: bool\n229: ```\n230: \n231: The `is_symlink` field SHALL be `true` if the path itself is a symbolic link (checked via `os.Lstat`).\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Stat a regular file\n234: \n235: - **GIVEN** a file `workspaceDir/test.txt` with size 100 bytes, mode `0644`\n236: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/stat?path=test.txt`\n237: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 200 with `{\"name\": \"test.txt\", \"size\": 100, \"mode\": \"0644\", \"mod_time\": \"...\", \"is_dir\": false, \"is_symlink\": false}`\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Stat a directory\n240: \n241: - **GIVEN** directory `workspaceDir/src/` exists\n242: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/stat?path=src`\n243: - **THEN** the response has `is_dir: true`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Stat a symlink\n246: \n247: - **GIVEN** a symlink `workspaceDir/link` pointing to `test.txt`\n248: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/stat?path=link`\n249: - **THEN** the response has `is_symlink: true`\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Path not found\n252: \n253: - **GIVEN** `path` does not exist\n254: - **WHEN** `os.Lstat` returns `os.IsNotExist`\n255: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"File not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Path traversal blocked\n258: \n259: - **GIVEN** `path` is `\"../../../etc/shadow\"`\n260: - **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n261: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with access denied error\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: DeleteFile API\n264: \n265: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files/delete` with JSON body containing `path` (string) or `paths` ([]string). A single `path` SHALL delete one file or empty directory. `paths` SHALL perform batch deletion of up to `MaxBatchSize` entries.\n266: \n267: ```\n268: DeleteFileRequest:\n269:   path:  string   (optional, single path)\n270:   paths: []string (optional, batch paths)\n271: ```\n272: \n273: Batch deletion SHALL use transactional semantics: if any single deletion fails, the handler SHALL continue with remaining paths and report partial results. The response SHALL indicate which paths succeeded and which failed.\n274: \n275: ```\n276: DeleteFileResponse:\n277:   deleted: []string (successfully deleted paths)\n278:   failed:  []DeleteFailure (paths that failed)\n279: \n280: DeleteFailure:\n281:   path:  string\n282:   error: string\n283: ```\n284: \n285: Directories SHALL only be deleted if empty (use `os.Remove`, not `os.RemoveAll`). Non-empty directories SHALL return an error in `failed`.\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Delete a single file\n288: \n289: - **GIVEN** file `workspaceDir/tmp.txt` exists\n290: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/files/delete` with `{\"path\": \"tmp.txt\"}`\n291: - **THEN** the file is removed and response is HTTP 200 with `{\"deleted\": [\"tmp.txt\"], \"failed\": []}`\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Delete non-existent file\n294: \n295: - **GIVEN** file `workspaceDir/ghost.txt` does not exist\n296: - **WHEN** the client calls `{\"path\": \"ghost.txt\"}`\n297: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"File not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Batch delete all succeed\n300: \n301: - **GIVEN** files `a.txt`, `b.txt`, `c.txt` exist\n302: - **WHEN** the client calls `{\"paths\": [\"a.txt\", \"b.txt\", \"c.txt\"]}`\n303: - **THEN** all three files are deleted and `deleted` contains all three paths\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Batch delete partial failure\n306: \n307: - **GIVEN** files `a.txt`, `c.txt` exist but `b.txt` does not\n308: - **WHEN** the client calls `{\"paths\": [\"a.txt\", \"b.txt\", \"c.txt\"]}`\n309: - **THEN** `a.txt` and `c.txt` are deleted, `deleted` contains `[\"a.txt\", \"c.txt\"]`, and `failed` contains `{\"path\": \"b.txt\", \"error\": \"File not found\"}`\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Batch delete exceeds MaxBatchSize\n312: \n313: - **GIVEN** `MaxBatchSize` is `100` and client sends `101` paths\n314: - **WHEN** the handler validates the request\n315: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `{\"error\": \"Batch size exceeds maximum of 100\", \"code\": 400}`\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: Delete non-empty directory fails\n318: \n319: - **GIVEN** directory `workspaceDir/logs/` contains files\n320: - **WHEN** the client calls `{\"path\": \"logs\"}`\n321: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with error indicating directory is not empty\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: Delete empty directory succeeds\n324: \n325: - **GIVEN** empty directory `workspaceDir/empty/` exists\n326: - **WHEN** the client calls `{\"path\": \"empty\"}`\n327: - **THEN** the directory is removed and response indicates success\n328: \n329: ### Requirement: MoveFile API\n330: \n331: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files/move` with JSON body to rename or move a file or directory.\n332: \n333: ```\n334: MoveFileRequest:\n335:   source:      string (required)\n336:   destination: string (required)\n337: ```\n338: \n339: The handler SHALL use `os.Rename` for the operation. If the destination's parent directory does not exist, the handler SHALL return an error (no automatic parent creation).\n340: \n341: ```\n342: MoveFileResponse:\n343:   source:      string\n344:   destination: string\n345: ```\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: Move file within workspace\n348: \n349: - **GIVEN** file `workspaceDir/old.txt` exists\n350: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/files/move` with `{\"source\": \"old.txt\", \"destination\": \"new.txt\"}`\n351: - **THEN** the file is renamed and response is HTTP 200 with `{\"source\": \"old.txt\", \"destination\": \"new.txt\"}`\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Move to subdirectory\n354: \n355: - **GIVEN** file `workspaceDir/a.txt` exists and directory `workspaceDir/sub/` exists\n356: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"source\": \"a.txt\", \"destination\": \"sub/a.txt\"}`\n357: - **THEN** the file is moved to `sub/a.txt`\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: Source does not exist\n360: \n361: - **GIVEN** `source` path does not exist\n362: - **WHEN** the handler calls `os.Rename`\n363: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"Source file not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: Destination parent does not exist\n366: \n367: - **GIVEN** directory `workspaceDir/nonexistent/` does not exist\n368: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"source\": \"a.txt\", \"destination\": \"nonexistent/a.txt\"}`\n369: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with error describing the failure\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Move escapes workspace\n372: \n373: - **GIVEN** `destination` is `\"../../etc/hostname\"`\n374: - **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called on destination\n375: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with access denied error\n376: \n377: ### Requirement: MkDir API\n378: \n379: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files/mkdir` with JSON body to create a directory (recursively).\n380: \n381: ```\n382: MkDirRequest:\n383:   path: string (required)\n384:   mode: string (optional, octal string, default: \"0755\")\n385: ```\n386: \n387: The handler SHALL use `os.MkdirAll` to create the directory and all parent directories.\n388: \n389: ```\n390: MkDirResponse:\n391:   path: string (relative to workspace)\n392:   created: bool (true if created, false if already existed)\n393: ```\n394: \n395: #### Scenario: Create new directory\n396: \n397: - **GIVEN** directory `workspaceDir/a/b/` does not exist\n398: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/files/mkdir` with `{\"path\": \"a/b\"}`\n399: - **THEN** directories `a/` and `a/b/` are created with mode `0755` and response has `created: true`\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Directory already exists\n402: \n403: - **GIVEN** directory `workspaceDir/existing/` exists\n404: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"existing\"}`\n405: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 200 with `created: false` and no error\n406: \n407: #### Scenario: Create with custom mode\n408: \n409: - **GIVEN** directory does not exist\n410: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"secret\", \"mode\": \"0700\"}`\n411: - **THEN** the directory is created with mode `0700`\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: Path is an existing file\n414: \n415: - **GIVEN** `workspaceDir/file.txt` is a regular file\n416: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"file.txt\"}`\n417: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with error indicating path already exists as a file\n418: \n419: ### Requirement: SearchFiles API\n420: \n421: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files/search` with JSON body to search for files matching a glob pattern within a directory tree.\n422: \n423: ```\n424: SearchFilesRequest:\n425:   path:        string (required, search root directory)\n426:   pattern:     string (required, glob pattern)\n427:   max_results: int    (optional, default: from config MaxSearchResults)\n428: ```\n429: \n430: The handler SHALL use `filepath.WalkDir` to traverse the directory tree rooted at `path`, matching entry names against `pattern` using `path.Match`. Traversal SHALL respect `MaxSearchDepth` (default 50) to limit directory depth. Results SHALL be limited to `max_results` entries.\n431: \n432: ```\n433: SearchFilesResponse:\n434:   matches:   []FileInfo\n435:   truncated: bool (true if results were limited by max_results)\n436: ```\n437: \n438: `FileInfo` in search results SHALL include the relative path from the workspace root.\n439: \n440: #### Scenario: Find matching files\n441: \n442: - **GIVEN** workspace contains `src/main.go`, `src/util.go`, `src/test/main_test.go`\n443: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/files/search` with `{\"path\": \"src\", \"pattern\": \"*.go\"}`\n444: - **THEN** the response contains `matches` for `src/main.go` and `src/util.go` (not `main_test.go`)\n445: \n446: #### Scenario: Recursive glob pattern\n447: \n448: - **GIVEN** workspace contains `a/1.txt`, `a/b/2.txt`, `a/b/c/3.txt`\n449: - **WHEN** the client calls with `{\"path\": \"a\", \"pattern\": \"*.txt\"}`\n450: - **THEN** all three `.txt` files are returned\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: Results truncated\n453: \n454: - **GIVEN** `MaxSearchResults` is `2` and 5 files match the pattern\n455: - **WHEN** the handler runs\n456: - **THEN** `matches` contains 2 entries and `truncated` is `true`\n457: \n458: #### Scenario: No matches\n459: \n460: - **GIVEN** no files match the pattern\n461: - **WHEN** the handler runs\n462: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 200 with `{\"matches\": [], \"truncated\": false}`\n463: \n464: #### Scenario: Search root does not exist\n465: \n466: - **GIVEN** `path` does not exist\n467: - **WHEN** the handler checks the search root\n468: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"Directory not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n469: \n470: #### Scenario: Search root is a file\n471: \n472: - **GIVEN** `path` points to a regular file\n473: - **WHEN** the handler checks the search root\n474: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with error indicating path is not a directory\n475: \n476: #### Scenario: Invalid glob pattern\n477: \n478: - **GIVEN** `pattern` is an invalid glob (e.g. `\"*[`)\n479: - **WHEN** `path.Match` is called\n480: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with error describing the invalid pattern\n481: \n482: #### Scenario: Depth limit respected\n483: \n484: - **GIVEN** a directory tree 60 levels deep and `MaxSearchDepth` is `50`\n485: - **WHEN** the handler walks the tree\n486: - **THEN** directories beyond depth 50 are not traversed\n487: \n488: ### Requirement: Chmod API\n489: \n490: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files/chmod` with JSON body to change file or directory permissions.\n491: \n492: ```\n493: ChmodRequest:\n494:   path: string (required)\n495:   mode: string (required, octal string, e.g. \"0755\")\n496: ```\n497: \n498: The handler SHALL parse the octal mode string and call `os.Chmod` on the sanitized path.\n499: \n500: ```\n501: ChmodResponse:\n502:   path: string\n503:   mode: string (the applied mode as octal string)\n504: ```\n505: \n506: #### Scenario: Change file permissions\n507: \n508: - **GIVEN** file `workspaceDir/script.sh` with mode `0644`\n509: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/files/chmod` with `{\"path\": \"script.sh\", \"mode\": \"0755\"}`\n510: - **THEN** the file mode is changed to `0755` and response is HTTP 200 with `{\"path\": \"script.sh\", \"mode\": \"0755\"}`\n511: \n512: #### Scenario: Invalid mode format\n513: \n514: - **GIVEN** `mode` is `\"abc\"`\n515: - **WHEN** the handler parses the mode\n516: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with error describing invalid mode format\n517: \n518: #### Scenario: Mode exceeds max\n519: \n520: - **GIVEN** `mode` is `\"07777\"` (exceeds `0777`)\n521: - **WHEN** the handler validates the mode\n522: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with error indicating mode is out of range\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: Path does not exist\n525: \n526: - **GIVEN** `path` does not exist\n527: - **WHEN** `os.Chmod` is called\n528: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"File not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n529: \n530: ### Requirement: Chunked upload support\n531: \n532: UploadFileHandler SHALL support chunked transfer via HTTP headers `X-Chunk-Index` (0-based) and `X-Chunk-Total` (total number of chunks). When chunk headers are present, the handler SHALL write each chunk to a temporary file and merge on the final chunk.\n533: \n534: For multipart chunked upload:\n535: - Each chunk SHALL include form field `chunk_index` and `chunk_total` in addition to `path` and `file`\n536: - Chunks SHALL be written to a temporary file named `<path>.chunk.<index>` in a temp directory\n537: - When `chunk_index == chunk_total - 1`, all chunks SHALL be concatenated in order and written to the final path\n538: - Temporary chunk files SHALL be cleaned up after merge or on error\n539: \n540: For JSON Base64 chunked upload:\n541: - Each request SHALL include `chunk_index` and `chunk_total` fields in the JSON body\n542: - Same temp file and merge behavior as multipart\n543: \n544: #### Scenario: Single chunk upload (no chunk headers)\n545: \n546: - **GIVEN** no `X-Chunk-Index` or `X-Chunk-Total` headers\n547: - **WHEN** the upload handler runs\n548: - **THEN** the file is written directly (existing behavior, no temp files)\n549: \n550: #### Scenario: Multi-chunk upload completes\n551: \n552: - **GIVEN** a file split into 3 chunks\n553: - **WHEN** the client sends chunk 0, then chunk 1, then chunk 2 (with `X-Chunk-Total: 3`)\n554: - **THEN** after chunk 2, the final file contains the concatenated content of all 3 chunks in order\n555: \n556: #### Scenario: Chunk out of order\n557: \n558: - **GIVEN** chunks arrive in order 2, 0, 1\n559: - **WHEN** all 3 chunks are received\n560: - **THEN** the final file is correctly assembled in order 0, 1, 2\n561: \n562: #### Scenario: Chunk exceeds MaxChunkSize\n563: \n564: - **GIVEN** `MaxChunkSize` is `1048576` (1 MiB) and a chunk body is `2097152` bytes\n565: - **WHEN** the handler checks the chunk size\n566: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 413 with `{\"error\": \"Chunk size exceeds maximum\", \"code\": 413}`\n567: \n568: #### Scenario: Temp files cleaned up after merge\n569: \n570: - **GIVEN** a 3-chunk upload completes successfully\n571: - **WHEN** the temp directory is inspected\n572: - **THEN** no `.chunk.*` files remain\n573: \n574: ### Requirement: Chunked download support\n575: \n576: DownloadFileHandler SHALL support HTTP `Range` requests for partial file downloads. When a `Range` header is present (format: `bytes=start-end`), the handler SHALL respond with HTTP 206 Partial Content and the requested byte range.\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Full download without Range header\n579: \n580: - **GIVEN** a file of 1000 bytes\n581: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/download?path=file.bin` without `Range` header\n582: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 200 with the full 1000 bytes and `Content-Length: 1000`\n583: \n584: #### Scenario: Partial download with Range header\n585: \n586: - **GIVEN** a file of 1000 bytes\n587: - **WHEN** the client calls with `Range: bytes=0-499`\n588: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 206 with `Content-Range: bytes 0-499/1000`, `Content-Length: 500`, and the first 500 bytes\n589: \n590: #### Scenario: Range from offset to end\n591: \n592: - **GIVEN** a file of 1000 bytes\n593: - **WHEN** the client calls with `Range: bytes=500-`\n594: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 206 with bytes 500-999 (500 bytes)\n595: \n596: #### Scenario: Range beyond file size\n597: \n598: - **GIVEN** a file of 100 bytes\n599: - **WHEN** the client calls with `Range: bytes=200-300`\n600: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 416 with `{\"error\": \"Range not satisfiable\", \"code\": 416}`\n601: \n602: ### Requirement: files/ subpackage structure\n603: \n604: The system SHALL refactor file management logic from `pkg/picod/files.go` into `pkg/picod/files/` subpackage. The subpackage SHALL export a `FileManager` interface and individual handler constructors.\n605: \n606: ```\n607: pkg/picod/files/\n608: ├── manager.go      — FileManager interface + implementation\n609: ├── read.go         — ReadFileHandler\n610: ├── write.go        — WriteFileHandler\n611: ├── stat.go         — StatFileHandler\n612: ├── list.go         — ListFilesHandler (migrated from AR-015)\n613: ├── upload.go       — UploadFileHandler (migrated from AR-015, with chunk support)\n614: ├── download.go     — DownloadFileHandler (migrated from AR-015, with Range support)\n615: ├── delete.go       — DeleteFileHandler\n616: ├── move.go         — MoveFileHandler\n617: ├── mkdir.go        — MkDirHandler\n618: ├── search.go       — SearchFilesHandler\n619: ├── chmod.go        — ChmodHandler\n620: └── types.go        — Request/Response structs, constants\n621: ```\n622: \n623: The `FileManager` interface SHALL encapsulate all file operations and accept a sanitized workspace root path. Handlers SHALL be methods on a struct that embeds or holds a `FileManager`.\n624: \n625: #### Scenario: FileManager interface exists\n626: \n627: - **GIVEN** the `pkg/picod/files/` package\n628: - **WHEN** the package is compiled\n629: - **THEN** a `FileManager` interface is exported with methods for read, write, stat, list, upload, download, delete, move, mkdir, search, and chmod\n630: \n631: #### Scenario: Old files.go is removed\n632: \n633: - **GIVEN** AR-016 is complete\n634: - **WHEN** `pkg/picod/files.go` is inspected\n635: - **THEN** the file no longer exists (logic migrated to `files/` subpackage)\n636: \n637: #### Scenario: Server routes use files/ package handlers\n638: \n639: - **GIVEN** `NewServer` is called\n640: - **WHEN** routes are registered\n641: - **THEN** file management routes point to handlers from the `files` subpackage\n642: \n643: ### Requirement: New request/response type definitions\n644: \n645: The system SHALL define the following structs in `pkg/picod/files/types.go` with exact JSON tags:\n646: \n647: ```go\n648: type ReadFileRequest struct {\n649:     Path   string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n650:     Offset int64  `json:\"offset\"`\n651:     Limit  int64  `json:\"limit\"`\n652: }\n653: \n654: type ReadFileResponse struct {\n655:     Content    string `json:\"content\"`\n656:     TotalSize  int64  `json:\"total_size\"`\n657:     ReadBytes  int64  `json:\"read_bytes\"`\n658: }\n659: \n660: type WriteFileRequest struct {\n661:     Path         string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n662:     Content      string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n663:     Offset       int64  `json:\"offset\"`\n664:     Mode         string `json:\"mode\"`\n665:     CreateParent bool   `json:\"create_parent\"`\n666: }\n667: \n668: type WriteFileResponse struct {\n669:     Path         string `json:\"path\"`\n670:     Size         int64  `json:\"size\"`\n671:     BytesWritten int64  `json:\"bytes_written\"`\n672: }\n673: \n674: type StatFileResponse struct {\n675:     Name      string    `json:\"name\"`\n676:     Size      int64     `json:\"size\"`\n677:     Mode      string    `json:\"mode\"`\n678:     ModTime   time.Time `json:\"mod_time\"`\n679:     IsDir     bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n680:     IsSymlink bool      `json:\"is_symlink\"`\n681: }\n682: \n683: type DeleteFileRequest struct {\n684:     Path  string   `json:\"path\"`\n685:     Paths []string `json:\"paths\"`\n686: }\n687: \n688: type DeleteFileResponse struct {\n689:     Deleted []string       `json:\"deleted\"`\n690:     Failed  []DeleteFailure `json:\"failed\"`\n691: }\n692: \n693: type DeleteFailure struct {\n694:     Path  string `json:\"path\"`\n695:     Error string `json:\"error\"`\n696: }\n697: \n698: type MoveFileRequest struct {\n699:     Source      string `json:\"source\" binding:\"required\"`\n700:     Destination string `json:\"destination\" binding:\"required\"`\n701: }\n702: \n703: type MoveFileResponse struct {\n704:     Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n705:     Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n706: }\n707: \n708: type MkDirRequest struct {\n709:     Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n710:     Mode string `json:\"mode\"`\n711: }\n712: \n713: type MkDirResponse struct {\n714:     Path    string `json:\"path\"`\n715:     Created bool   `json:\"created\"`\n716: }\n717: \n718: type SearchFilesRequest struct {\n719:     Path       string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n720:     Pattern    string `json:\"pattern\" binding:\"required\"`\n721:     MaxResults int    `json:\"max_results\"`\n722: }\n723: \n724: type SearchFilesResponse struct {\n725:     Matches   []FileEntry `json:\"matches\"`\n726:     Truncated bool        `json:\"truncated\"`\n727: }\n728: \n729: type ChmodRequest struct {\n730:     Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n731:     Mode string `json:\"mode\" binding:\"required\"`\n732: }\n733: \n734: type ChmodResponse struct {\n735:     Path string `json:\"path\"`\n736:     Mode string `json:\"mode\"`\n737: }\n738: ```\n739: \n740: #### Scenario: ReadFileRequest binding\n741: \n742: - **GIVEN** JSON body `{\"path\": \"data.bin\", \"offset\": 100, \"limit\": 50}`\n743: - **WHEN** `ShouldBindJSON` is called\n744: - **THEN** all fields are populated with correct types\n745: \n746: #### Scenario: DeleteFileRequest with single path\n747: \n748: - **GIVEN** JSON body `{\"path\": \"tmp.txt\"}`\n749: - **WHEN** `ShouldBindJSON` is called\n750: - **THEN** `Path` is `\"tmp.txt\"` and `Paths` is nil/empty\n751: \n752: #### Scenario: DeleteFileRequest with batch paths\n753: \n754: - **GIVEN** JSON body `{\"paths\": [\"a.txt\", \"b.txt\"]}`\n755: - **WHEN** `ShouldBindJSON` is called\n756: - **THEN** `Paths` contains two elements and `Path` is empty\n757: \n758: #### Scenario: SearchFilesRequest defaults\n759: \n760: - **GIVEN** JSON body `{\"path\": \"src\", \"pattern\": \"*.go\"}` without `max_results`\n761: - **WHEN** `ShouldBindJSON` is called\n762: - **THEN** `MaxResults` is `0` (handler shall apply config default)\n763: \n764: ### Requirement: Error response consistency\n765: \n766: All file management endpoints SHALL use a consistent error response format matching AR-015:\n767: \n768: ```json\n769: {\"error\": \"<human-readable message>\", \"code\": <http_status_code>}\n770: ```\n771: \n772: The following HTTP status codes SHALL be used:\n773: \n774: | Code | Condition |\n775: |------|-----------|\n776: | 400 | Invalid request (bad path, bad format, missing required field, path traversal) |\n777: | 404 | File or directory not found |\n778: | 409 | Conflict (e.g., destination exists during move) |\n779: | 413 | Request body or chunk too large |\n780: | 416 | Range not satisfiable |\n781: | 500 | Internal server error (file system operation failure) |\n782: \n783: #### Scenario: Consistent 400 response for path traversal\n784: \n785: - **GIVEN** any file management endpoint\n786: - **WHEN** a path traversal attempt is detected\n787: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 400 with `{\"error\": \"Invalid path: access denied: workspace jail violation\", \"code\": 400}`\n788: \n789: #### Scenario: Consistent 404 response for missing file\n790: \n791: - **GIVEN** any endpoint that reads a file\n792: - **WHEN** the file does not exist\n793: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"File not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n794: \n795: #### Scenario: 413 for oversized request body\n796: \n797: - **GIVEN** a request body exceeds `MaxBodySize` (32 MiB)\n798: - **WHEN** the JWT middleware wraps the body with `http.MaxBytesReader`\n799: - **THEN** the handler receives a read error and responds HTTP 413\n800: \n801: ### Requirement: Path sanitization reuse\n802: \n803: All file management handlers SHALL use the same `sanitizePath` function from AR-015. The function SHALL be moved to the `files/` subpackage or made accessible to it. All path inputs SHALL be sanitized before any file system operation.\n804: \n805: #### Scenario: All endpoints sanitize paths\n806: \n807: - **GIVEN** any file management endpoint\n808: - **WHEN** a request with `path` containing `\"..\"` is received\n809: - **THEN** `sanitizePath` is called before any file operation\n810: \n811: #### Scenario: Workspace jail is enforced across all endpoints\n812: \n813: - **GIVEN** a symlink inside the workspace pointing outside\n814: - **WHEN** any endpoint resolves the symlink path\n815: - **THEN** the re-verification step detects the escape and returns access denied\n816: \n817: ### Requirement: Backward compatibility with AR-015 tests\n818: \n819: All existing tests for AR-015 file operations (upload, list, download) SHALL continue to pass after refactoring. Test files SHALL be updated to import from the `files/` subpackage where necessary.\n820: \n821: #### Scenario: AR-015 upload tests pass\n822: \n823: - **GIVEN** the refactored codebase\n824: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/picod/... -run Upload` is run\n825: - **THEN** all upload-related tests pass\n826: \n827: #### Scenario: AR-015 list tests pass\n828: \n829: - **GIVEN** the refactored codebase\n830: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/picod/... -run List` is run\n831: - **THEN** all list-related tests pass\n832: \n833: #### Scenario: AR-015 download tests pass\n834: \n835: - **GIVEN** the refactored codebase\n836: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/picod/... -run Download` is run\n837: - **THEN** all download-related tests pass\n838: \n839: #### Scenario: AR-015 sanitize tests pass\n840: \n841: - **GIVEN** the refactored codebase\n842: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/picod/... -run Sanitize` is run\n843: - **THEN** all path sanitization tests pass\n844: \n845: ### Requirement: Code quality gates\n846: \n847: The codebase SHALL pass the following checks after AR-016 implementation:\n848: \n849: - `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` produces no warnings\n850: - `go test ./pkg/picod/...` passes all tests\n851: - `go mod tidy` results in no changes (no unused dependencies)\n852: - All new handlers have unit tests covering normal, error, and edge cases\n853: \n854: #### Scenario: go vet clean\n855: \n856: - **GIVEN** AR-016 is implemented\n857: - **WHEN** `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` is run\n858: - **THEN** no warnings or errors are reported\n859: \n860: #### Scenario: All tests pass\n861: \n862: - **GIVEN** AR-016 is implemented\n863: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/picod/...` is run\n864: - **THEN** all tests pass with exit code 0\n865: \n866: #### Scenario: No unused dependencies\n867: \n868: - **GIVEN** AR-016 is implemented\n869: - **WHEN** `go mod tidy` is run\n870: - **THEN** `go.mod` and `go.sum` are unchanged\n\n(End of file - total 870 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016: PicoD 文件管理 API — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/picod`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `code-execution/spec.md`, `delta-spec.md` (AR-015), `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Route table reorganization\n\nThe system SHALL reorganize file management routes under explicit sub-paths. The following routes SHALL exist under the `/api` group with JWT auth middleware:\n\n| Method | Path | Handler |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| POST | `/api/files/read` | ReadFileHandler |\n| POST | `/api/files/write` | WriteFileHandler |\n| GET | `/api/files/stat` | StatFileHandler |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775841754830,"end":1775841754837}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841756241,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786abfce001T1Ve4CulVr2pBa","messageID":"msg_d786aad2b001moFrHKB7LouY1F","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_269b5035208a48dbac2ed285","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package picod\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"fmt\"\n5: \t\"net/http\"\n6: \t\"os\"\n7: \t\"path/filepath\"\n8: \t\"time\"\n9: \n10: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n11: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n12: )\n13: \n14: type Server struct {\n15: \tengine       *gin.Engine\n16: \tconfig       Config\n17: \tauthManager  *AuthManager\n18: \tstartTime    time.Time\n19: \tworkspaceDir string\n20: }\n21: \n22: func NewServer(config Config) *Server {\n23: \tgin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n24: \tengine := gin.New()\n25: \tengine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())\n26: \n27: \tauthManager := newAuthManager()\n28: \tif err := authManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv(); err != nil {\n29: \t\tcheckFatal(err)\n30: \t}\n31: \n32: \tworkspaceDir := config.Workspace\n33: \tif workspaceDir == \"\" {\n34: \t\tcwd, err := os.Getwd()\n35: \t\tif err != nil {\n36: \t\t\tklog.Fatalf(\"failed to get current working directory: %v\", err)\n37: \t\t}\n38: \t\tworkspaceDir = cwd\n39: \t} else {\n40: \t\tabsPath, err := filepath.Abs(workspaceDir)\n41: \t\tif err != nil {\n42: \t\t\tklog.Fatalf(\"failed to resolve workspace path: %v\", err)\n43: \t\t}\n44: \t\tworkspaceDir = absPath\n45: \t}\n46: \n47: \ts := &Server{\n48: \t\tengine:       engine,\n49: \t\tconfig:       config,\n50: \t\tauthManager:  authManager,\n51: \t\tstartTime:    time.Now(),\n52: \t\tworkspaceDir: workspaceDir,\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \ts.registerRoutes()\n56: \n57: \treturn s\n58: }\n59: \n60: func (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n61: \tapi := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\n62: \tapi.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n63: \t{\n64: \t\tapi.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n65: \t\tapi.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n66: \t\tapi.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n67: \t\tapi.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n68: \t}\n69: \ts.engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n70: }\n71: \n72: func (s *Server) Run() error {\n73: \tserver := &http.Server{\n74: \t\tAddr:              fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", s.config.Port),\n75: \t\tHandler:           s.engine,\n76: \t\tReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n77: \t}\n78: \treturn server.ListenAndServe()\n79: }\n80: \n81: func (s *Server) HealthCheckHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n82: \tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\n83: \t\t\"status\":  \"ok\",\n84: \t\t\"service\": \"PicoD\",\n85: \t\t\"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n86: \t\t\"uptime\":  time.Since(s.startTime).String(),\n87: \t})\n88: }\n\n(End of file - total 88 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package picod\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\ntype Server struct {\n\tengine       *gin.Engine\n\tconfig       Config\n\tauthManager  *AuthManager\n\tstartTime    time.Time\n\tworkspaceDir string\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go","time":{"start":1775841756233,"end":1775841756239}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841757453,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786ac4d9001dXDErccVDl9cPJ","messageID":"msg_d786aad2b001moFrHKB7LouY1F","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_80946e56f11c49f0aec0179f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package picod\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"encoding/base64\"\n5: \t\"fmt\"\n6: \t\"io\"\n7: \t\"mime\"\n8: \t\"net/http\"\n9: \t\"os\"\n10: \t\"path/filepath\"\n11: \t\"strconv\"\n12: \t\"strings\"\n13: \n14: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n15: )\n16: \n17: func (s *Server) sanitizePath(p string) (string, error) {\n18: \tif s.workspaceDir == \"\" {\n19: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"workspace directory not initialized\")\n20: \t}\n21: \n22: \tresolvedWorkspace, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(s.workspaceDir)\n23: \tif err != nil {\n24: \t\tresolvedWorkspace, err = filepath.Abs(s.workspaceDir)\n25: \t\tif err != nil {\n26: \t\t\tresolvedWorkspace = filepath.Clean(s.workspaceDir)\n27: \t\t}\n28: \t}\n29: \tresolvedWorkspace = filepath.Clean(resolvedWorkspace)\n30: \n31: \tcleanPath := filepath.Clean(p)\n32: \tif filepath.IsAbs(cleanPath) {\n33: \t\tcleanPath = strings.TrimPrefix(cleanPath, string(os.PathSeparator))\n34: \t}\n35: \n36: \tfullPathCandidate := filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(resolvedWorkspace, cleanPath))\n37: \n38: \trelPath, relErr := filepath.Rel(resolvedWorkspace, fullPathCandidate)\n39: \tif relErr != nil {\n40: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"access denied: workspace jail violation\")\n41: \t}\n42: \tsep := string(os.PathSeparator)\n43: \tif strings.HasPrefix(relPath, \"..\"+sep) || relPath == \"..\" {\n44: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"access deni