{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841767051,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786aea94001w9dFjIfrf6C4gv","messageID":"msg_d786acde1001RnZGYqCSzZYsJy","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_561d7dab33ea4128b681dbd1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012: Session Store Interface Definition — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: The `pkg/store` package provides a pluggable session storage abstraction for AgentCube sandbox metadata. It persists sandbox information keyed by session ID, maintains sorted-set indices for expiry-based and activity-based garbage collection, and supports Redis or Valkey backends selected at runtime via `STORE_TYPE`.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Provider Selection Flow\n10: \n11: ```\n12: STORE_TYPE (env, case-insensitive)\n13:     │\n14:     ├── unset / \"redis\"   → redisStore  (go-redis/v9)\n15:     ├── \"valkey\"          → valkeyStore (valkey-io/valkey-go)\n16:     └── other             → initStore() error\n17: ```\n18: \n19: ### 1.3 Data Flow\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │               Caller (GC Controller / Router)         │\n24: └──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n25:                        │\n26:                        ▼\n27: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n28: │                  store.Storage()                      │\n29: │             (sync.Once singleton accessor)            │\n30: └──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n31:                        │\n32:             ┌──────────┴──────────┐\n33:             ▼                     ▼\n34: ┌─────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────┐\n35: │    redisStore       │ │    valkeyStore      │\n36: │  go-redis/v9        │ │  valkey-io/valkey   │\n37: └─────────┬───────────┘ └─────────┬───────────┘\n38:           │                       │\n39:           ▼                       ▼\n40: ┌─────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────┐\n41: │      Redis          │ │      Valkey         │\n42: │ session:{id} (JSON) │ │ session:{id} (JSON) │\n43: │ session:expiry      │ │ session:expiry      │\n44: │  (ZSET: score=exp)  │ │  (ZSET: score=exp)  │\n45: │ session:last_activity│ │session:last_activity│\n46: │  (ZSET: score=ts)   │ │  (ZSET: score=ts)   │\n47: └─────────────────────┘ └─────────────────────┘\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### 1.4 Package Layout\n51: \n52: ```\n53: pkg/store/\n54: ├── store.go                  # Store interface, ErrNotFound\n55: ├── singleton.go              # Storage(), initStore(), sync.Once, type constants\n56: ├── store_redis.go            # redisStore implementation\n57: ├── store_valkey.go           # valkeyStore implementation\n58: ├── store_test.go             # Singleton & provider selection tests\n59: ├── store_redis_test.go       # Redis unit tests\n60: └── store_valkey_test.go      # Valkey unit tests\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n64: \n65: | Module | Purpose |\n66: |--------|---------|\n67: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n68: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n69: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging (Valkey options, fatal init) |\n70: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` type definition |\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 2. Data Structures\n75: \n76: ### 2.1 Store Interface\n77: \n78: ```go\n79: package store\n80: \n81: import (\n82:     \"context\"\n83:     \"time\"\n84: \n85:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n86: )\n87: \n88: type Store interface {\n89:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n90:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n91:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n92:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n93:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n94:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n95:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n96:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n97:     Close() error\n98: }\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### 2.2 Sentinel Errors\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ### 2.3 Provider Type Constants\n108: \n109: ```go\n110: const (\n111:     redisStoreType  = \"redis\"\n112:     valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"\n113: )\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### 2.4 Singleton State\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: var (\n120:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n121:     provider      Store\n122: )\n123: \n124: func Storage() Store\n125: func initStore() error\n126: ```\n127: \n128: - `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error → `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n129: \n130: ### 2.5 Sandbox Document Type\n131: \n132: Stored as JSON, unmarshals to `pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: type SandboxInfo struct {\n136:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n137:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n138:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n139:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n140:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n141:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n142:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n143:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n144:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n145: }\n146: \n147: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n148:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n149:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n150:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### 2.6 Redis Implementation Struct\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: type redisStore struct {\n158:     cli                  *redisv9.Client\n159:     sessionPrefix        string\n160:     expiryIndexKey       string\n161:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n162: }\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ### 2.7 Valkey Implementation Struct\n166: \n167: ```go\n168: type valkeyStore struct {\n169:     cli                  valkey.Client\n170:     sessionPrefix        string\n171:     expiryIndexKey       string\n172:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n173: }\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ### 2.8 Key Constants (Both Implementations)\n177: \n178: | Field | Value | Purpose |\n179: |-------|-------|---------|\n180: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session JSON string keys |\n181: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET key for expiry-based GC |\n182: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET key for activity-based GC |\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## 3. API Contracts\n187: \n188: ### 3.1 Method Specifications\n189: \n190: #### Ping\n191: \n192: | Aspect | Detail |\n193: |--------|--------|\n194: | Redis | `PING` → expect `PONG` string response |\n195: | Valkey | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n196: | Error | Backend connection error propagated |\n197: \n198: #### GetSandboxBySessionID\n199: \n200: | Aspect | Detail |\n201: |--------|--------|\n202: | Key | `session:{sessionID}` |\n203: | Redis | `GET` → `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n204: | Valkey | `B().Get().Key(key)` → `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n205: | Success | JSON unmarshal → `*types.SandboxInfo` |\n206: \n207: #### StoreSandbox\n208: \n209: | Aspect | Detail |\n210: |--------|--------|\n211: | Validation | Reject nil sandbox; reject zero `ExpiresAt` |\n212: | Redis | Pipeline: `SETNX session:{id} <json>`, `ZADD session:expiry <score> <id>`, `ZADD session:last_activity <now> <id>` |\n213: | Valkey | `DoMulti`: same three commands |\n214: | ZSET scores | Expiry: `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())`; Activity: `float64(time.Now().Unix())` |\n215: | Atomicity | All commands in one pipeline; any failure aborts batch |\n216: \n217: #### UpdateSandbox\n218: \n219: | Aspect | Detail |\n220: |--------|--------|\n221: | Redis | `SET key value XX` (key must exist); false → `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` |\n222: | Valkey | `SET ... XX`; response `ToString() != \"OK\"` → same error |\n223: | Side effects | Does NOT modify ZSET entries |\n224: \n225: #### DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n226: \n227: | Aspect | Detail |\n228: |--------|--------|\n229: | Redis | Pipeline: `DEL session:{id}`, `ZREM session:expiry {id}`, `ZREM session:last_activity {id}` |\n230: | Valkey | `DoMulti`: same three commands |\n231: \n232: #### ListExpiredSandboxes\n233: \n234: | Aspect | Detail |\n235: |--------|--------|\n236: | Precondition | `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil` |\n237: | Redis | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 limit` → pipeline GETs |\n238: | Valkey | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` → `Mget` |\n239: | Missing keys | Orphan ZSET members (no corresponding JSON key) are skipped, not errors |\n240: \n241: #### ListInactiveSandboxes\n242: \n243: | Aspect | Detail |\n244: |--------|--------|\n245: | Same as ListExpiredSandboxes, but queries `session:last_activity` ZSET |\n246: \n247: #### UpdateSessionLastActivity\n248: \n249: | Aspect | Detail |\n250: |--------|--------|\n251: | Validation | Reject empty `sessionID`; if `at.IsZero()` use `time.Now()` |\n252: | Precondition | Session key must exist; absent → `ErrNotFound` |\n253: | Redis | `EXISTS session:{id}` → must be 1; then `ZADD session:last_activity <score> <id>` |\n254: | Valkey | `Exists` → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n255: \n256: #### Close\n257: \n258: | Aspect | Detail |\n259: |--------|--------|\n260: | Redis | `cli.Close()` |\n261: | Valkey | `vs.cli.Close()` → return nil |\n262: \n263: ### 3.2 ZSET Score Semantics\n264: \n265: | Index | Score Source | When Set |\n266: |-------|-------------|----------|\n267: | `session:expiry` | `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n268: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n269: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(at.Unix())` (or now if zero) | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n270: \n271: ### 3.3 Error Handling Matrix\n272: \n273: | Scenario | Error Returned | Notes |\n274: |----------|---------------|-------|\n275: | Session key not found | `ErrNotFound` | Both backends normalize |\n276: | Nil sandbox to StoreSandbox | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` | Input validation |\n277: | Zero ExpiresAt | `errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")` | Input validation |\n278: | Empty sessionID | `errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")` | UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n279: | UpdateSandbox missing key | `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` | SET XX fails |\n280: | Pipeline command failure | Backend error | Batch aborts |\n281: | Unsupported STORE_TYPE | `fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %q\", storeType)` | initStore |\n282: | Missing REDIS_ADDR | `errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")` | Redis init |\n283: | Missing REDIS_PASSWORD | `errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required ...\")` | Unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n284: | Missing VALKEY_ADDR | `errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")` | Valkey init |\n285: | Missing VALKEY_PASSWORD | `errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required ...\")` | Unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ## 4. Core Implementation\n290: \n291: ### 4.1 Singleton (`singleton.go`)\n292: \n293: ```go\n294: func Storage() Store {\n295:     initStoreOnce.Do(func() {\n296:         if err := initStore(); err != nil {\n297:             klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)\n298:         }\n299:     })\n300:     return provider\n301: }\n302: \n303: func initStore() error {\n304:     storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n305:     if storeType == \"\" {\n306:         storeType = redisStoreType\n307:     }\n308:     switch storeType {\n309:     case redisStoreType:\n310:         s, err := newRedisStore()\n311:         if err != nil {\n312:             return err\n313:         }\n314:         provider = s\n315:     case valkeyStoreType:\n316:         s, err := newValkeyStore()\n317:         if err != nil {\n318:             return err\n319:         }\n320:         provider = s\n321:     default:\n322:         return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %q\", storeType)\n323:     }\n324:     return nil\n325: }\n326: ```\n327: \n328: ### 4.2 Redis Constructor (`store_redis.go`)\n329: \n330: ```go\n331: func newRedisStore() (*redisStore, error) {\n332:     redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n333:     if redisAddr == \"\" {\n334:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n335:     }\n336: \n337:     redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n338:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n339:     if redisPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n340:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n341:     }\n342: \n343:     opts := &redisv9.Options{\n344:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n345:         Password: redisPassword,\n346:     }\n347: \n348:     cli := redisv9.NewClient(opts)\n349:     if err := cli.Ping(context.Background()).Err(); err != nil {\n350:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"redis ping failed: %w\", err)\n351:     }\n352: \n353:     return &redisStore{\n354:         cli:                  cli,\n355:         sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n356:         expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n357:         lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n358:     }, nil\n359: }\n360: ```\n361: \n362: ### 4.3 Redis Key Helper\n363: \n364: ```go\n365: func (rs *redisStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n366:     return rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n367: }\n368: ```\n369: \n370: ### 4.4 Redis StoreSandbox\n371: \n372: ```go\n373: func (rs *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n374:     if sandbox == nil {\n375:         return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n376:     }\n377:     if sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n378:         return errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n379:     }\n380: \n381:     data, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n382:     if err != nil {\n383:         return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n384:     }\n385: \n386:     key := rs.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n387:     now := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n388:     expiryScore := float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n389: \n390:     pipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n391:     pipe.SetNX(ctx, key, data, 0)\n392:     pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, redisv9.Z{Score: expiryScore, Member: sandbox.SessionID})\n393:     pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, redisv9.Z{Score: now, Member: sandbox.SessionID})\n394: \n395:     _, err = pipe.Exec(ctx)\n396:     return err\n397: }\n398: ```\n399: \n400: ### 4.5 Redis Load Helper\n401: \n402: ```go\n403: func (rs *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n404:     if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n405:         return nil, nil\n406:     }\n407: \n408:     keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n409:     for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n410:         keys[i] = rs.sessionKey(id)\n411:     }\n412: \n413:     results, err := rs.cli.MGet(ctx, keys...).Result()\n414:     if err != nil {\n415:         return nil, err\n416:     }\n417: \n418:     var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n419:     for _, raw := range results {\n420:         if raw == nil {\n421:             continue\n422:         }\n423:         data, ok := raw.(string)\n424:         if !ok || data == \"\" {\n425:             continue\n426:         }\n427:         var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n428:         if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n429:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n430:         }\n431:         sandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n432:     }\n433:     return sandboxes, nil\n434: }\n435: ```\n436: \n437: ### 4.6 Valkey Constructor (`store_valkey.go`)\n438: \n439: ```go\n440: func newValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, error) {\n441:     valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n442:     if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n443:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n444:     }\n445: \n446:     valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n447:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n448:     if valkeyPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n449:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n450:     }\n451: \n452:     opts := &valkey.ClientOption{\n453:         InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n454:         Password:    valkeyPassword,\n455:     }\n456: \n457:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n458:         if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n459:             opts.DisableCache = true\n460:         }\n461:     }\n462:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n463:         if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n464:             opts.ForceSingleClient = true\n465:         }\n466:     }\n467: \n468:     cli, err := valkey.NewClient(opts)\n469:     if err != nil {\n470:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"create valkey client: %w\", err)\n471:     }\n472: \n473:     pong, err := cli.Do(context.Background(), cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n474:     if err != nil || pong != \"PONG\" {\n475:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"valkey ping failed: %w\", err)\n476:     }\n477: \n478:     klog.V(2).Infof(\"valkey client initialized: addr=%s, disableCache=%v, forceSingle=%v\",\n479:         valkeyAddr, opts.DisableCache, opts.ForceSingleClient)\n480: \n481:     return &valkeyStore{\n482:         cli:                  cli,\n483:         sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n484:         expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n485:         lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n486:     }, nil\n487: }\n488: ```\n489: \n490: ### 4.7 Valkey Load Helper\n491: \n492: > **Note:** Keys should be in the same slot for cluster deployments to use MGET efficiently.\n493: \n494: ```go\n495: func (vs *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n496:     if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n497:         return nil, nil\n498:     }\n499: \n500:     keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n501:     for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n502:         keys[i] = vs.sessionKey(id)\n503:     }\n504: \n505:     results, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, vs.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n506:     if err != nil {\n507:         return nil, err\n508:     }\n509: \n510:     var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n511:     for _, data := range results {\n512:         if data == \"\" {\n513:             continue\n514:         }\n515:         var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n516:         if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n517:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n518:         }\n519:         sandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n520:     }\n521:     return sandboxes, nil\n522: }\n523: ```\n524: \n525: ---\n526: \n527: ## 5. Environment Variables\n528: \n529: ### 5.1 Redis\n530: \n531: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n532: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n533: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | — | Redis server address |\n534: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | — | Auth password |\n535: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n536: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `redis` for this backend |\n537: \n538: ### 5.2 Valkey\n539: \n540: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n541: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n542: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | — | Comma-separated → `InitAddress` |\n543: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | — | Auth password |\n544: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n545: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | `\"true\"` → `DisableCache` |\n546: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | `\"true\"` → `ForceSingleClient` |\n547: | `STORE_TYPE` | Yes | — | Must be `valkey` for this backend |\n548: \n549: ---\n550: \n551: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n552: \n553: ### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n554: \n555: #### Singleton & Provider Selection (`store_test.go`)\n556: \n557: | Test Name | Description |\n558: |-----------|-------------|\n559: | `TestStorage_DefaultsToRedis` | Unset `STORE_TYPE` → redisStore |\n560: | `TestStorage_ValkeyProvider` | `STORE_TYPE=valkey` → valkeyStore |\n561: | `TestStorage_InvalidProvider` | `STORE_TYPE=unknown` → initStore error |\n562: | `TestStorage_ConcurrentAccess` | Multiple goroutines → exactly one init |\n563: \n564: #### Redis Implementation (`store_redis_test.go`)\n565: \n566: | Test Name | Description |\n567: |-----------|-------------|\n568: | `TestRedisStore_Ping_Success` | PING → PONG |\n569: | `TestRedisStore_Ping_Failure` | Connection error → propagated |\n570: | `TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found` | GET returns JSON → unmarshaled |\n571: | `TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | GET nil → `ErrNotFound` |\n572: | `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success` | Pipeline: SETNX + ZADD×2 succeed |\n573: | `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected` | nil sandbox → error |\n574: | `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` | Zero ExpiresAt → error |\n575: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_Success` | SETXX → OK |\n576: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | SETXX → false → error |\n577: | `TestRedisStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: DEL + ZREM×2 |\n578: | `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` | ZRANGEBYSCORE → MGET → sandboxes |\n579: | `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ZeroLimit` | limit=0 → nil, nil |\n580: | `TestRedisStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` | ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity |\n581: | `TestRedisStore_LoadSandboxes_SkipsOrphans` | MGET nil → skip orphan ZSET member |\n582: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_Success` | EXISTS=1 → ZADD |\n583: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound` | EXISTS=0 → `ErrNotFound` |\n584: | `TestRedisStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` | `at.IsZero()` → uses `time.Now()` |\n585: | `TestRedisStore_Close` | `cli.Close()` called |\n586: \n587: #### Valkey Implementation (`store_valkey_test.go`)\n588: \n589: | Test Name | Description |\n590: |-----------|-------------|\n591: | `TestValkeyStore_Ping_Success` | Ping → PONG |\n592: | `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found` | Get → bytes → unmarshaled |\n593: | `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n594: | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success` | DoMulti: SETNX + ZADD×2 |\n595: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_Success` | SET XX → \"OK\" |\n596: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | SET XX → not \"OK\" → error |\n597: | `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | DoMulti: DEL + ZREM×2 |\n598: | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` | Zrangebyscore → loadSandboxes |\n599: | `TestValkeyStore_LoadSandboxes_SkipsEmpty` | MGET \"\" → skip missing key |\n600: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity` | Exists=1 → Zadd |\n601: | `TestValkeyStore_Options_DisableCache` | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` → set |\n602: | `TestValkeyStore_Options_ForceSingle` | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true` → set |\n603: \n604: ### 6.2 Integration Tests\n605: \n606: | Test Name | Description |\n607: |-----------|-------------|\n608: | `TestRedisStore_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Store → Get → Update → List → Delete against real Redis |\n609: | `TestValkeyStore_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Same cycle against real Valkey |\n610: | `TestStore_GC_Workflow` | Store expired sandboxes, list and delete |\n611: \n612: ### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n613: \n614: - **Redis:** Use `miniredis` for in-memory Redis-compatible testing\n615: - **Valkey:** Use interface abstraction over `valkey.Client` with recorded command expectations\n616: - All tests run with `-race` flag for data race detection\n617: \n618: ### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n619: \n620: 1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n621: 2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n622: 3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n623: 4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n624: 5. No sensitive data in logs (passwords, connection strings)\n625: \n626: ---\n627: \n628: ## 7. Deployment Considerations\n629: \n630: 1. **Valkey Cluster Slot Affinity:** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` uses MGET which requires all keys to hash to the same slot in cluster mode. Consider hash tags (e.g., `session:{cluster}:id`) if deploying to Valkey Cluster.\n631: \n632: 2. **Password Policy:** Both backends require a password by default. Set `{BACKEND}_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` only in trusted network environments.\n633: \n634: 3. **ZSET Index Growth:** `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` sorted sets grow monotonically. Ensure the GC controller regularly calls `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` to prevent unbounded growth.\n635: \n636: 4. **Connection Pooling:** Both clients use default connection pool settings. Tune via environment-specific configuration if needed.\n637: \n638: ---\n639: \n640: ## 8. Implementation Steps\n641: \n642: ### Phase 1: Interface & Singleton (Day 1)\n643: \n644: 1. Define `Store` interface in `store.go`\n645: 2. Define `ErrNotFound` sentinel error\n646: 3. Implement singleton pattern in `singleton.go` with provider selection\n647: 4. Write `store_test.go` for singleton and provider selection\n648: \n649: ### Phase 2: Redis Implementation (Day 2)\n650: \n651: 1. Implement `redisStore` struct and constructor in `store_redis.go`\n652: 2. Implement all Store interface methods\n653: 3. Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper\n654: 4. Write `store_redis_test.go` with miniredis\n655: \n656: ### Phase 3: Valkey Implementation (Day 3)\n657: \n658: 1. Implement `valkeyStore` struct and constructor in `store_valkey.go`\n659: 2. Implement all Store interface methods\n660: 3. Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper\n661: 4. Write `store_valkey_test.go`\n662: \n663: ### Phase 4: Integration & Gate (Day 4)\n664: \n665: 1. Run `go build ./pkg/store/...`\n666: 2. Run `go test ./pkg/store/... -v`\n667: 3. Run `go test -race ./pkg/store/...`\n668: 4. Verify no sensitive data in logs\n669: 5. Fix all issues\n670: \n671: ---\n672: \n673: ## 9. Future Changes\n674: \n675: | Change | Description | Priority |\n676: |--------|-------------|----------|\n677: | AR-0XX | TTL on session keys for automatic cleanup | P1 |\n678: | AR-0XX | Hash tag support for Valkey Cluster slot affinity | P2 |\n679: | AR-0XX | Metrics: store operation latency, error rates | P2 |\n680: | AR-0XX | Additional backend support (e.g., etcd, DynamoDB) | P3 |\n681: \n682: ### Known Limitations\n683: \n684: - No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup\n685: - MGET in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` assumes single-slot keys for cluster deployments\n686: - No pagination for `List*` methods beyond simple `limit` parameter\n687: - Singleton pattern does not support re-initialization or hot-swapping backends\n\n(End of file - total 687 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012: Session Store Interface Definition — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `pkg/store` package provides a pluggable session storage abstraction for AgentCube sandbox metadata. It persists sandbox information keyed by session ID, maintains sorted-set indices for expiry-based and activity-based garbage collection, and supports Redis or Valkey backends selected at runtime via `STORE_TYPE`.\n\n### 1.2 Provider Selection Flow\n\n```\nSTORE_TYPE (env, case-insensitive)\n    │\n    ├── unset / \"redis\"   → redisStore  (go-redis/v9)\n    ├── \"valkey\"          → valkeyStore (valkey-io/valkey-go)\n    └── other             → initStore() error\n```\n\n### 1.3 Data Flow\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775841767044,"end":1775841767049}}}}
