{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775841769223,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786af70400112cCWiJp3SAH4B","messageID":"msg_d786aeeea0011OgAN1srsWkHdT","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775842023466,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786b0590001wK1z8KGAeg7sjX","messageID":"msg_d786aeeea0011OgAN1srsWkHdT","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed. Let me write the design.md file.","time":{"start":1775842023464,"end":1775842023464}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842023476,"sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","part":{"id":"prt_d786b0765001l8LlXHRuonRnad","messageID":"msg_d786aeeea0011OgAN1srsWkHdT","sessionID":"ses_287982ba7ffe6OpW4s4gTpMr7K","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_555a19093b854c398e2e0620","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-016: PicoD File Management API — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `pkg/picod/files/` subpackage provides a comprehensive file management API for the PicoD in-sandbox daemon. It replaces the monolithic `files.go` with a structured subpackage that exports a `FileManager` interface and individual HTTP handlers for read, write, stat, list, upload, download, delete, move, mkdir, search, and chmod operations. All operations are constrained within a workspace jail via path sanitization and protected by JWT authentication.\n\n### 1.2 Route Reorganization\n\nThe file management routes are reorganized from legacy wildcard/overloaded paths to explicit sub-paths under `/api/files/`:\n\n```\nLegacy (AR-015)                  →  AR-016\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nPOST /api/files (upload)         →  POST /api/files/upload\nGET  /api/files (list)           →  GET  /api/files (with ?path query)\nGET  /api/files/*path (download) →  GET  /api/files/download?path=...\n                                  +  POST /api/files/read\n                                  +  POST /api/files/write\n                                  +  GET  /api/files/stat?path=...\n                                  +  POST /api/files/delete\n                                  +  POST /api/files/move\n                                  +  POST /api/files/mkdir\n                                  +  POST /api/files/search\n                                  +  POST /api/files/chmod\n```\n\n### 1.3 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Client (Router/SDK)                        │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │ JWT-protected HTTP\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Gin Engine (/api)                         │\n│              AuthMiddleware (JWT RS256 verify)                │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   FileHandler (server.go)                     │\n│      Routes to files/ subpackage handlers via FileManager     │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    FileManager                                │\n│  ┌─────────┬──────────┬──────────┬──────────┬─────────────┐  │\n│  │ Read    │ Write    │ Stat     │ List     │ Upload      │  │\n│  │ Download│ Delete   │ Move     │ MkDir    │ Search      │  │\n│  │ Chmod   │          │          │          │             │  │\n│  └────┬────┴────┬─────┴────┬─────┴────┬─────┴──────┬──────┘  │\n│       │         │          │          │            │          │\n│       ▼         ▼          ▼          ▼            ▼          │\n│  sanitizePath → workspace jail → os.* operations              │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│               Filesystem (sandbox workspace)                  │\n│         workspaceDir (config.Workspace, resolved abs)         │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.4 Package Layout\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── server.go              — Server struct, route registration (updated)\n├── config.go              — Config struct (extended with file management fields)\n├── types.go               — ExecuteRequest/Response, legacy types (retained)\n├── auth.go                — AuthManager (unchanged)\n├── execute.go             — ExecuteHandler (unchanged)\n├── files/                 — New file management subpackage\n│   ├── manager.go         — FileManager interface + implementation\n│   ├── types.go           — Request/Response structs, constants\n│   ├── sanitize.go        — sanitizePath (migrated from files.go)\n│   ├── read.go            — ReadFileHandler\n│   ├── write.go           — WriteFileHandler\n│   ├── stat.go            — StatFileHandler\n│   ├── list.go            — ListFilesHandler (migrated from AR-015)\n│   ├── upload.go          — UploadFileHandler (migrated, with chunk support)\n│   ├── download.go        — DownloadFileHandler (migrated, with Range support)\n│   ├── delete.go          — DeleteFileHandler\n│   ├── move.go            — MoveFileHandler\n│   ├── mkdir.go           — MkDirHandler\n│   ├── search.go          — SearchFilesHandler\n│   └── chmod.go           — ChmodHandler\n├── server_test.go         — Server-level tests (updated routes)\n├── config_test.go         — Config parsing tests (updated)\n├── auth_test.go           — Auth tests (unchanged)\n├── execute_test.go        — Execute tests (unchanged)\n├── sanitize_test.go       — Path sanitization tests (moved to files/)\n├── health_test.go         — Health check tests (unchanged)\n└── files/                 — File subpackage tests\n    ├── manager_test.go    — FileManager integration tests\n    ├── sanitize_test.go   — Path sanitization tests\n    ├── read_test.go       — ReadFile tests\n    ├── write_test.go      — WriteFile tests\n    ├── stat_test.go       — StatFile tests\n    ├── list_test.go       — ListFiles tests\n    ├── upload_test.go     — Upload tests (incl. chunked)\n    ├── download_test.go   — Download tests (incl. Range)\n    ├── delete_test.go     — Delete tests (incl. batch)\n    ├── move_test.go       — Move tests\n    ├── mkdir_test.go      — MkDir tests\n    ├── search_test.go     — Search tests\n    └── chmod_test.go      — Chmod tests\n```\n\n### 1.5 Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework, request binding |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `encoding/base64` | Base64 encoding/decoding for read/write |\n| `path/filepath` | Path manipulation, sanitization |\n| `os` | File system operations |\n| `io`, `mime`, `net/http` | File serving, content type detection |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Config Extension\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port             int    `json:\"port\"`\n    Workspace        string `json:\"workspace\"`\n    MaxChunkSize     int64  `json:\"max_chunk_size\"`      // default: 32 << 20 (32 MiB)\n    MaxBatchSize     int    `json:\"max_batch_size\"`      // default: 100\n    MaxSearchResults int    `json:\"max_search_results\"`  // default: 100\n    MaxSearchDepth   int    `json:\"max_search_depth\"`    // default: 50\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 FileManager Interface\n\n```go\ntype FileManager interface {\n    ReadFile(ctx context.Context, req *ReadFileRequest) (*ReadFileResponse, error)\n    WriteFile(ctx context.Context, req *WriteFileRequest) (*WriteFileResponse, error)\n    StatFile(ctx context.Context, path string) (*StatFileResponse, error)\n    ListFiles(ctx context.Context, path string) (*ListFilesResponse, error)\n    UploadFile(ctx context.Context, req *UploadFileRequest) (*FileInfo, error)\n    UploadFileChunked(ctx context.Context, req *ChunkedUploadRequest) (*FileInfo, error)\n    DownloadFile(ctx context.Context, req *DownloadFileRequest) (*DownloadFileResponse, error)\n    DeleteFile(ctx context.Context, req *DeleteFileRequest) (*DeleteFileResponse, error)\n    MoveFile(ctx context.Context, req *MoveFileRequest) (*MoveFileResponse, error)\n    MkDir(ctx context.Context, req *MkDirRequest) (*MkDirResponse, error)\n    SearchFiles(ctx context.Context, req *SearchFilesRequest) (*SearchFilesResponse, error)\n    Chmod(ctx context.Context, req *ChmodRequest) (*ChmodResponse, error)\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3 Request/Response Types (`files/types.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ReadFileRequest struct {\n    Path   string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Offset int64  `json:\"offset\"`\n    Limit  int64  `json:\"limit\"`\n}\n\ntype ReadFileResponse struct {\n    Content   string `json:\"content\"`\n    TotalSize int64  `json:\"total_size\"`\n    ReadBytes int64  `json:\"read_bytes\"`\n}\n\ntype WriteFileRequest struct {\n    Path         string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Content      string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Offset       int64  `json:\"offset\"`\n    Mode         string `json:\"mode\"`\n    CreateParent bool   `json:\"create_parent\"`\n}\n\ntype WriteFileResponse struct {\n    Path         string `json:\"path\"`\n    Size         int64  `json:\"size\"`\n    BytesWritten int64  `json:\"bytes_written\"`\n}\n\ntype StatFileResponse struct {\n    Name      string    `json:\"name\"`\n    Size      int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Mode      string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    ModTime   time.Time `json:\"mod_time\"`\n    IsDir     bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n    IsSymlink bool      `json:\"is_symlink\"`\n}\n\ntype ListFilesResponse struct {\n    Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n}\n\ntype FileEntry struct {\n    Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n}\n\ntype UploadFileRequest struct {\n    Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n}\n\ntype ChunkedUploadRequest struct {\n    Path       string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Content    string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Mode       string `json:\"mode\"`\n    ChunkIndex int    `json:\"chunk_index\"`\n    ChunkTotal int    `json:\"chunk_total\"`\n}\n\ntype DownloadFileRequest struct {\n    Path  string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Range string `json:\"-\"` // from HTTP Range header\n}\n\ntype DownloadFileResponse struct {\n    Content       []byte\n    ContentType   string\n    ContentLength int64\n    StatusCode    int // 200 or 206\n    ContentRange  string\n}\n\ntype DeleteFileRequest struct {\n    Path  string   `json:\"path\"`\n    Paths []string `json:\"paths\"`\n}\n\ntype DeleteFileResponse struct {\n    Deleted []string        `json:\"deleted\"`\n    Failed  []DeleteFailure `json:\"failed\"`\n}\n\ntype DeleteFailure struct {\n    Path  string `json:\"path\"`\n    Error string `json:\"error\"`\n}\n\ntype MoveFileRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\" binding:\"required\"`\n}\n\ntype MoveFileResponse struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n\ntype MkDirRequest struct {\n    Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Mode string `json:\"mode\"`\n}\n\ntype MkDirResponse struct {\n    Path    string `json:\"path\"`\n    Created bool   `json:\"created\"`\n}\n\ntype SearchFilesRequest struct {\n    Path       string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Pattern    string `json:\"pattern\" binding:\"required\"`\n    MaxResults int    `json:\"max_results\"`\n}\n\ntype SearchFilesResponse struct {\n    Matches   []FileEntry `json:\"matches\"`\n    Truncated bool        `json:\"truncated\"`\n}\n\ntype ChmodRequest struct {\n    Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Mode string `json:\"mode\" binding:\"required\"`\n}\n\ntype ChmodResponse struct {\n    Path string `json:\"path\"`\n    Mode string `json:\"mode\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 2.4 FileManager Implementation Struct\n\n```go\ntype fileManager struct {\n    workspaceDir     string\n    resolvedWorkspace string\n    maxChunkSize     int64\n    maxBatchSize     int\n    maxSearchResults int\n    maxSearchDepth   int\n    tempDir          string // for chunked uploads\n}\n```\n\n### 2.5 Constants (`files/types.go`)\n\n| Constant | Value | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `DefaultMaxChunkSize` | `32 << 20` (33554432) | Default max chunk size (32 MiB) |\n| `DefaultMaxBatchSize` | `100` | Default max batch operation size |\n| `DefaultMaxSearchResults` | `100` | Default max search results |\n| `DefaultMaxSearchDepth` | `50` | Default max directory depth for search |\n| `DefaultDirMode` | `\"0755\"` | Default directory creation mode |\n| `DefaultFileMode` | `\"0644\"` | Default file creation mode |\n| `MaxFileMode` | `0777` | Maximum valid file mode |\n| `ChunkExt` | `\".chunk\"` | Suffix for temporary chunk files |\n\n### 2.6 Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrPathTraversal     = errors.New(\"access denied: workspace jail violation\")\n    ErrFileNotFound      = errors.New(\"file not found\")\n    ErrDirectoryNotFound = errors.New(\"directory not found\")\n    ErrIsDirectory       = errors.New(\"path is a directory, not a file\")\n    ErrNotADirectory     = errors.New(\"path is not a directory\")\n    ErrInvalidBase64     = errors.New(\"invalid base64 content\")\n    ErrInvalidMode       = errors.New(\"invalid mode format\")\n    ErrModeOutOfRange    = errors.New(\"mode exceeds maximum allowed value\")\n    ErrChunkTooLarge     = errors.New(\"chunk size exceeds maximum\")\n    ErrRangeNotSatisfiable = errors.New(\"range not satisfiable\")\n    ErrBatchSizeExceeded = errors.New(\"batch size exceeds maximum\")\n    ErrDirectoryNotEmpty = errors.New(\"directory is not empty\")\n    ErrPathAlreadyExists = errors.New(\"path already exists as a file\")\n    ErrWorkspaceNotInitialized = errors.New(\"workspace directory not initialized\")\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Route Table\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Auth |\n|--------|------|---------|------|\n| POST | `/api/execute` | ExecuteHandler | JWT |\n| POST | `/api/files/read` | ReadFileHandler | JWT |\n| POST | `/api/files/write` | WriteFileHandler | JWT |\n| GET | `/api/files/stat` | StatFileHandler | JWT |\n| GET | `/api/files` | ListFilesHandler | JWT |\n| POST | `/api/files/upload` | UploadFileHandler | JWT |\n| GET | `/api/files/download` | DownloadFileHandler | JWT |\n| POST | `/api/files/delete` | DeleteFileHandler | JWT |\n| POST | `/api/files/move` | MoveFileHandler | JWT |\n| POST | `/api/files/mkdir` | MkDirHandler | JWT |\n| POST | `/api/files/search` | SearchFilesHandler | JWT |\n| POST | `/api/files/chmod` | ChmodHandler | JWT |\n| GET | `/health` | HealthCheckHandler | None |\n\n### 3.2 ReadFile API\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/read`\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"hello.txt\",\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"limit\": -1\n}\n```\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"content\": \"<base64 encoded content>\",\n  \"total_size\": 13,\n  \"read_bytes\": 13\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Opens file at sanitized path\n- Seeks to `offset` (negative treated as 0)\n- Reads up to `limit` bytes; if `limit < 0`, reads to EOF\n- Base64-encodes content\n- If offset exceeds file size: returns empty content, `read_bytes: 0`\n- If path is directory: HTTP 400 `ErrIsDirectory`\n- If file not found: HTTP 404 `ErrFileNotFound`\n\n### 3.3 WriteFile API\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/write`\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"data.txt\",\n  \"content\": \"<base64 encoded>\",\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"mode\": \"overwrite\",\n  \"create_parent\": false\n}\n```\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"data.txt\",\n  \"size\": 11,\n  \"bytes_written\": 11\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Decodes Base64 content\n- `mode=\"overwrite\"`, `offset=0`: truncate and replace\n- `mode=\"overwrite\"`, `offset>0`: seek to offset, overwrite in place (no truncation beyond written data)\n- `mode=\"append\"`: append to end (offset ignored)\n- `create_parent=true`: create parent directories with mode 0755\n- If path is directory: HTTP 400 `ErrIsDirectory`\n- If invalid Base64: HTTP 400 `ErrInvalidBase64`\n\n### 3.4 StatFile API\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/files/stat?path=...`\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"test.txt\",\n  \"size\": 100,\n  \"mode\": \"0644\",\n  \"mod_time\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"is_dir\": false,\n  \"is_symlink\": false\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Uses `os.Lstat` to detect symlinks\n- Returns metadata for file or directory\n- If path not found: HTTP 404 `ErrFileNotFound`\n\n### 3.5 ListFiles API\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/files?path=...`\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\"name\": \"src\", \"size\": 4096, \"modified\": \"...\", \"mode\": \"drwxr-xr-x\", \"is_dir\": true},\n    {\"name\": \"readme.md\", \"size\": 1024, \"modified\": \"...\", \"mode\": \"-rw-r--r--\", \"is_dir\": false}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Requires `path` query parameter\n- Lists directory contents\n- If path missing: HTTP 400\n- If path not found: HTTP 404\n- If path is not a directory: HTTP 400\n\n### 3.6 UploadFile API\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/upload`\n\n**Content Types:**\n- `multipart/form-data`: form fields `path`, `file`, optional `mode`, `chunk_index`, `chunk_total`\n- `application/json`: JSON body with `UploadFileRequest` or `ChunkedUploadRequest`\n\n**Chunked Upload (multipart):**\n- Headers: `X-Chunk-Index`, `X-Chunk-Total`\n- Form fields: `chunk_index`, `chunk_total`\n- Chunks written to `<tempDir>/<path>.chunk.<index>`\n- Final chunk triggers merge: concatenate chunks in order, write to final path\n- Temp files cleaned up after merge or on error\n\n**Chunked Upload (JSON):**\n- Body includes `chunk_index`, `chunk_total` fields\n- Same temp file and merge behavior\n\n**Chunk Size Validation:**\n- If chunk body exceeds `MaxChunkSize`: HTTP 413 `ErrChunkTooLarge`\n\n### 3.7 DownloadFile API\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/files/download?path=...`\n\n**Range Request Support:**\n- If `Range` header present (format: `bytes=start-end`):\n  - Parse range\n  - If range satisfiable: HTTP 206 with `Content-Range`, partial content\n  - If range beyond file size: HTTP 416 `ErrRangeNotSatisfiable`\n- If no `Range` header: HTTP 200 with full content\n\n**Response Headers:**\n- `Content-Type`: detected from file extension or `application/octet-stream`\n- `Content-Disposition`: `attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`\n- `Content-Description`: `File Transfer`\n- `Content-Transfer-Encoding`: `binary`\n- For 206: `Content-Range: bytes start-end/total`\n\n### 3.8 DeleteFile API\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/delete`\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\"path\": \"tmp.txt\"}\n// or\n{\"paths\": [\"a.txt\", \"b.txt\", \"c.txt\"]}\n```\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"deleted\": [\"a.txt\", \"c.txt\"],\n  \"failed\": [{\"path\": \"b.txt\", \"error\": \"file not found\"}]\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Single `path`: delete one file or empty directory\n- `paths`: batch delete up to `MaxBatchSize` entries\n- Uses `os.Remove` (not `os.RemoveAll`) — directories must be empty\n- Batch: continues on failure, reports partial results\n- If batch exceeds `MaxBatchSize`: HTTP 400 `ErrBatchSizeExceeded`\n\n### 3.9 MoveFile API\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/move`\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"source\": \"old.txt\",\n  \"destination\": \"new.txt\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"source\": \"old.txt\",\n  \"destination\": \"new.txt\"\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Uses `os.Rename`\n- Both source and destination sanitized against workspace\n- If source not found: HTTP 404\n- If destination parent not found: HTTP 400\n- If destination escapes workspace: HTTP 400 `ErrPathTraversal`\n\n### 3.10 MkDir API\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/mkdir`\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"a/b/c\",\n  \"mode\": \"0755\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"a/b/c\",\n  \"created\": true\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Uses `os.MkdirAll`\n- If directory already exists: `created: false`, no error\n- If path is existing file: HTTP 400 `ErrPathAlreadyExists`\n- Default mode: `0755`\n\n### 3.11 SearchFiles API\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/search`\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"src\",\n  \"pattern\": \"*.go\",\n  \"max_results\": 50\n}\n```\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"matches\": [\n    {\"name\": \"main.go\", \"size\": 1024, \"modified\": \"...\", \"mode\": \"-rw-r--r--\", \"is_dir\": false}\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": false\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Uses `filepath.WalkDir` to traverse directory tree\n- Matches entry names against `pattern` using `path.Match`\n- Respects `MaxSearchDepth` (default 50) — directories beyond depth skipped\n- Results limited to `max_results` (default from config)\n- If search root not found: HTTP 404\n- If search root is file: HTTP 400 `ErrNotADirectory`\n- If invalid glob pattern: HTTP 400\n\n### 3.12 Chmod API\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/chmod`\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"script.sh\",\n  \"mode\": \"0755\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response Body (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"script.sh\",\n  \"mode\": \"0755\"\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Parses octal mode string (base 8)\n- Validates mode ≤ 0777\n- Calls `os.Chmod` on sanitized path\n- If invalid mode format: HTTP 400 `ErrInvalidMode`\n- If mode > 0777: HTTP 400 `ErrModeOutOfRange`\n- If path not found: HTTP 404\n\n### 3.13 Error Response Format\n\nAll endpoints use consistent error format:\n\n```json\n{\"error\": \"<human-readable message>\", \"code\": <http_status_code>}\n```\n\n**HTTP Status Code Matrix:**\n\n| Code | Condition |\n|------|-----------|\n| 400 | Invalid request (bad path, bad format, missing required field, path traversal, directory where file expected, invalid mode, invalid glob) |\n| 404 | File or directory not found |\n| 409 | Conflict (destination exists during move) |\n| 413 | Request body or chunk too large |\n| 416 | Range not satisfiable |\n| 500 | Internal server error (file system operation failure) |\n\n### 3.14 Path Sanitization\n\nAll path inputs pass through `sanitizePath`:\n\n1. Strip leading `/` from absolute paths\n2. `filepath.Clean` to normalize\n3. Join with resolved workspace directory\n4. Verify result is within workspace via `filepath.Rel`\n5. `filepath.EvalSymlinks` on final candidate\n6. Re-verify symlink-resolved path is within workspace\n7. If any check fails: return `ErrPathTraversal`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Core Implementation\n\n### 4.1 FileManager Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc NewFileManager(workspaceDir string, cfg Config) (FileManager, error) {\n    resolved, err := filepath.Abs(workspaceDir)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    resolved, err = filepath.EvalSymlinks(resolved)\n    if err != nil {\n        resolved = filepath.Clean(resolved)\n    }\n\n    if cfg.MaxChunkSize <= 0 {\n        cfg.MaxChunkSize = DefaultMaxChunkSize\n    }\n    if cfg.MaxBatchSize <= 0 {\n        cfg.MaxBatchSize = DefaultMaxBatchSize\n    }\n    if cfg.MaxSearchResults <= 0 {\n        cfg.MaxSearchResults = DefaultMaxSearchResults\n    }\n    if cfg.MaxSearchDepth <= 0 {\n        cfg.MaxSearchDepth = DefaultMaxSearchDepth\n    }\n\n    tempDir := filepath.Join(os.TempDir(), \"picod-chunks\")\n    if err := os.MkdirAll(tempDir, 0700); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    return &fileManager{\n        workspaceDir:     workspaceDir,\n        resolvedWorkspace: resolved,\n        maxChunkSize:     cfg.MaxChunkSize,\n        maxBatchSize:     cfg.MaxBatchSize,\n        maxSearchResults: cfg.MaxSearchResults,\n        maxSearchDepth:   cfg.MaxSearchDepth,\n        tempDir:          tempDir,\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.2 sanitizePath (`files/sanitize.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (fm *fileManager) sanitizePath(p string) (string, error) {\n    if fm.resolvedWorkspace == \"\" {\n        return \"\", ErrWorkspaceNotInitialized\n    }\n\n    cleanPath := filepath.Clean(p)\n    if filepath.IsAbs(cleanPath) {\n        cleanPath = strings.TrimPrefix(cleanPath, string(os.PathSeparator))\n    }\n\n    fullPathCandidate := filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(fm.resolvedWorkspace, cleanPath))\n\n    relPath, relErr := filepath.Rel(fm.resolvedWorkspace, fullPathCandidate)\n    if relErr != nil {\n        return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n    }\n    sep := string(os.PathSeparator)\n    if strings.HasPrefix(relPath, \"..\"+sep) || relPath == \"..\" {\n        return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n    }\n\n    resolvedFinalPath, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPathCandidate)\n    if err == nil {\n        relPath2, relErr2 := filepath.Rel(fm.resolvedWorkspace, resolvedFinalPath)\n        if relErr2 != nil {\n            return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n        }\n        if strings.HasPrefix(relPath2, \"..\"+sep) || relPath2 == \"..\" {\n            return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n        }\n        return resolvedFinalPath, nil\n    }\n\n    return fullPathCandidate, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 ReadFile Implementation (`files/read.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (fm *fileManager) ReadFile(ctx context.Context, req *ReadFileRequest) (*ReadFileResponse, error) {\n    safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    info, err := os.Stat(safePath)\n    if err != nil {\n        if os.IsNotExist(err) {\n            return nil, ErrFileNotFound\n        }\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    if info.IsDir() {\n        return nil, ErrIsDirectory\n    }\n\n    f, err := os.Open(safePath)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    defer f.Close()\n\n    totalSize := info.Size()\n    offset := req.Offset\n    if offset < 0 {\n        offset = 0\n    }\n\n    if _, err := f.Seek(offset, io.SeekStart); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    var data []byte\n    if req.Limit < 0 {\n        data, err = io.ReadAll(f)\n    } else {\n        data = make([]byte, req.Limit)\n        n, err := f.Read(data)\n        data = data[:n]\n        if err != nil && err != io.EOF {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n    }\n\n    return &ReadFileResponse{\n        Content:   base64.StdEncoding.EncodeToString(data),\n        TotalSize: totalSize,\n        ReadBytes: int64(len(data)),\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.4 WriteFile Implementation (`files/write.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (fm *fileManager) WriteFile(ctx context.Context, req *WriteFileRequest) (*WriteFileResponse, error) {\n    data, err := base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(req.Content)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, ErrInvalidBase64\n    }\n\n    safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    info, statErr := os.Stat(safePath)\n    if statErr == nil && info.IsDir() {\n        return nil, ErrIsDirectory\n    }\n\n    if req.CreateParent {\n        if err := os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(safePath), 0755); err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n    }\n\n    var flags int\n    switch req.Mode {\n    case \"append\":\n        flags = os.O_CREATE | os.O_WRONLY | os.O_APPEND\n    default: // overwrite\n        if req.Offset > 0 {\n            flags = os.O_CREATE | os.O_WRONLY\n        } else {\n            flags = os.O_CREATE | os.O_WRONLY | os.O_TRUNC\n        }\n    }\n\n    fileMode := parseFileMode(req.Mode)\n    f, err := os.OpenFile(safePath, flags, fileMode)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    defer f.Close()\n\n    if req.Offset > 0 && req.Mode != \"append\" {\n        if _, err := f.Seek(req.Offset, io.SeekStart); err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n    }\n\n    n, err := f.Write(data)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    info, err = os.Stat(safePath)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    relPath, _ := filepath.Rel(fm.workspaceDir, safePath)\n    return &WriteFileResponse{\n        Path:         relPath,\n        Size:         info.Size(),\n        BytesWritten: int64(n),\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.5 Chunked Upload (`files/upload.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (fm *fileManager) handleChunkedUpload(ctx context.Context, req *ChunkedUploadRequest) (*FileInfo, error) {\n    data, err := base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(req.Content)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, ErrInvalidBase64\n    }\n\n    if int64(len(data)) > fm.maxChunkSize {\n        return nil, ErrChunkTooLarge\n    }\n\n    safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    chunkFileName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s.chunk.%d\", filepath.Base(safePath), req.ChunkIndex)\n    chunkPath := filepath.Join(fm.tempDir, chunkFileName)\n\n    if err := os.WriteFile(chunkPath, data, 0600); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    if req.ChunkIndex == req.ChunkTotal-1 {\n        return fm.mergeChunks(safePath, req.Path, req.ChunkTotal, parseFileMode(req.Mode))\n    }\n\n    relPath, _ := filepath.Rel(fm.workspaceDir, safePath)\n    return &FileInfo{\n        Path:     relPath,\n        Size:     int64(len(data)),\n        Mode:     \"0600\",\n        Modified: time.Now(),\n    }, nil\n}\n\nfunc (fm *fileManager) mergeChunks(finalPath, relPath string, totalChunks int, mode os.FileMode) (*FileInfo, error) {\n    defer fm.cleanupChunks(relPath, totalChunks)\n\n    final, err := os.OpenFile(finalPath, os.O_CREATE|os.O_WRONLY|os.O_TRUNC, mode)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    defer final.Close()\n\n    for i := 0; i < totalChunks; i++ {\n        chunkPath := filepath.Join(fm.tempDir, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s.chunk.%d\", filepath.Base(finalPath), i))\n        data, err := os.ReadFile(chunkPath)\n        if err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n        if _, err := final.Write(data); err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n    }\n\n    info, err := os.Stat(finalPath)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    relPathResp, _ := filepath.Rel(fm.workspaceDir, finalPath)\n    return &FileInfo{\n        Path:     relPathResp,\n        Size:     info.Size(),\n        Mode:     info.Mode().String(),\n        Modified: info.ModTime(),\n    }, nil\n}\n\nfunc (fm *fileManager) cleanupChunks(relPath string, totalChunks int) {\n    for i := 0; i < totalChunks; i++ {\n        chunkPath := filepath.Join(fm.tempDir, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s.chunk.%d\", filepath.Base(relPath), i))\n        os.Remove(chunkPath)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 4.6 Download with Range Support (`files/download.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (fm *fileManager) DownloadFile(ctx context.Context, req *DownloadFileRequest) (*DownloadFileResponse, error) {\n    safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    info, err := os.Stat(safePath)\n    if err != nil {\n        if os.IsNotExist(err) {\n            return nil, ErrFileNotFound\n        }\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    if info.IsDir() {\n        return nil, ErrIsDirectory\n    }\n\n    f, err := os.Open(safePath)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    totalSize := info.Size()\n\n    if req.Range != \"\" {\n        return fm.handleRangeRequest(f, req.Range, totalSize, safePath)\n    }\n\n    data, err := io.ReadAll(f)\n    f.Close()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    contentType := mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(safePath))\n    if contentType == \"\" {\n        contentType = \"application/octet-stream\"\n    }\n\n    return &DownloadFileResponse{\n        Content:       data,\n        ContentType:   contentType,\n        ContentLength: totalSize,\n        StatusCode:    http.StatusOK,\n    }, nil\n}\n\nfunc (fm *fileManager) handleRangeRequest(f *os.File, rangeHeader string, totalSize int64, path string) (*DownloadFileResponse, error) {\n    defer f.Close()\n\n    start, end, err := parseRange(rangeHeader, totalSize)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, ErrRangeNotSatisfiable\n    }\n\n    if start >= totalSize {\n        return nil, ErrRangeNotSatisfiable\n    }\n\n    if end >= totalSize {\n        end = totalSize - 1\n    }\n\n    length := end - start + 1\n    data := make([]byte, length)\n\n    if _, err := f.Seek(start, io.SeekStart); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    if _, err := io.ReadFull(f, data); err != nil && err != io.ErrUnexpectedEOF {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    contentType := mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))\n    if contentType == \"\" {\n        contentType = \"application/octet-stream\"\n    }\n\n    return &DownloadFileResponse{\n        Content:       data,\n        ContentType:   contentType,\n        ContentLength: length,\n        StatusCode:    http.StatusPartialContent,\n        ContentRange:  fmt.Sprintf(\"bytes %d-%d/%d\", start, end, totalSize),\n    }, nil\n}\n\nfunc parseRange(rangeHeader string, totalSize int64) (int64, int64, error) {\n    if !strings.HasPrefix(rangeHeader, \"bytes=\") {\n        return 0, 0, errors.New(\"invalid range format\")\n    }\n\n    rangeSpec := strings.TrimPrefix(rangeHeader, \"bytes=\")\n    parts := strings.SplitN(rangeSpec, \"-\", 2)\n    if len(parts) != 2 {\n        return 0, 0, errors.New(\"invalid range format\")\n    }\n\n    start, err := strconv.ParseInt(parts[0], 10, 64)\n    if err != nil {\n        return 0, 0, err\n    }\n\n    var end int64\n    if parts[1] == \"\" {\n        end = totalSize - 1\n    } else {\n        end, err = strconv.ParseInt(parts[1], 10, 64)\n        if err != nil {\n            return 0, 0, err\n        }\n    }\n\n    if start > end {\n        return 0, 0, errors.New(\"invalid range: start > end\")\n    }\n\n    return start, end, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.7 SearchFiles Implementation (`files/search.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (fm *fileManager) SearchFiles(ctx context.Context, req *SearchFilesRequest) (*SearchFilesResponse, error) {\n    safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    info, err := os.Stat(safePath)\n    if err != nil {\n        if os.IsNotExist(err) {\n            return nil, ErrDirectoryNotFound\n        }\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    if !info.IsDir() {\n        return nil, ErrNotADirectory\n    }\n\n    maxResults := req.MaxResults\n    if maxResults <= 0 {\n        maxResults = fm.maxSearchResults\n    }\n\n    baseDepth := strings.Count(safePath, string(os.PathSeparator))\n\n    var matches []FileEntry\n    var truncated bool\n\n    err = filepath.WalkDir(safePath, func(path string, d os.DirEntry, err error) error {\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n\n        depth := strings.Count(path, string(os.PathSeparator)) - baseDepth\n        if depth > fm.maxSearchDepth {\n            return filepath.SkipDir\n        }\n\n        matched, matchErr := path.Match(req.Pattern, d.Name())\n        if matchErr != nil {\n            return matchErr\n        }\n\n        if matched && !d.IsDir() {\n            info, err := d.Info()\n            if err != nil {\n                return nil\n            }\n\n            relPath, _ := filepath.Rel(fm.workspaceDir, path)\n            matches = append(matches, FileEntry{\n                Name:     relPath,\n                Size:     info.Size(),\n                Modified: info.ModTime(),\n                Mode:     info.Mode().String(),\n                IsDir:    false,\n            })\n\n            if len(matches) >= maxResults {\n                truncated = true\n                return errors.New(\"search complete\")\n            }\n        }\n\n        return nil\n    })\n\n    if err != nil && err.Error() != \"search complete\" {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    return &SearchFilesResponse{\n        Matches:   matches,\n        Truncated: truncated,\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4.8 Server Route Registration (updated `server.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n    fm, err := files.NewFileManager(s.workspaceDir, s.config.FileConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create file manager: %v\", err)\n    }\n    s.fileManager = fm\n\n    api := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\n    api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n    {\n        api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n\n        fileGroup := api.Group(\"/files\")\n        {\n            fileGroup.POST(\"/read\", s.ReadFileHandler)\n            fileGroup.POST(\"/write\", s.WriteFileHandler)\n            fileGroup.GET(\"/stat\", s.StatFileHandler)\n            fileGroup.GET(\"\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n            fileGroup.POST(\"/upload\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n            fileGroup.GET(\"/download\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n            fileGroup.POST(\"/delete\", s.DeleteFileHandler)\n            fileGroup.POST(\"/move\", s.MoveFileHandler)\n            fileGroup.POST(\"/mkdir\", s.MkDirHandler)\n            fileGroup.POST(\"/search\", s.SearchFilesHandler)\n            fileGroup.POST(\"/chmod\", s.ChmodHandler)\n        }\n    }\n    s.engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n}\n```\n\n### 4.9 Config Extension (`config.go`)\n\n```go\ntype FileConfig struct {\n    MaxChunkSize     int64 `json:\"max_chunk_size\"`\n    MaxBatchSize     int   `json:\"max_batch_size\"`\n    MaxSearchResults int   `json:\"max_search_results\"`\n    MaxSearchDepth   int   `json:\"max_search_depth\"`\n}\n\ntype Config struct {\n    Port      int        `json:\"port\"`\n    Workspace string     `json:\"workspace\"`\n    FileConfig FileConfig `json:\"file_config\"`\n}\n\nfunc ParseFlags() Config {\n    port := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"Port for the PicoD server to listen on\")\n    workspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Root directory for file operations\")\n    maxChunkSize := flag.Int64(\"max-chunk-size\", files.DefaultMaxChunkSize, \"Maximum size per chunk in bytes\")\n    maxBatchSize := flag.Int(\"max-batch-size\", files.DefaultMaxBatchSize, \"Maximum number of paths in batch operations\")\n    maxSearchResults := flag.Int(\"max-search-results\", files.DefaultMaxSearchResults, \"Maximum search results\")\n    maxSearchDepth := flag.Int(\"max-search-depth\", files.DefaultMaxSearchDepth, \"Maximum directory depth for search\")\n    flag.Parse()\n\n    return Config{\n        Port:      *port,\n        Workspace: *workspace,\n        FileConfig: FileConfig{\n            MaxChunkSize:     *maxChunkSize,\n            MaxBatchSize:     *maxBatchSize,\n            MaxSearchResults: *maxSearchResults,\n            MaxSearchDepth:   *maxSearchDepth,\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | Yes | — | RSA public key for JWT verification |\n| `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | No | cwd | Default workspace directory |\n| `PICOD_PORT` | No | 8080 | Server listen port |\n\nFile management limits are configured via CLI flags, not environment variables.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n\n#### Config Tests (`config_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestParseFlags_Defaults` | No flags → default values for all fields |\n| `TestParseFlags_CustomFileLimits` | `--max-chunk-size=16777216 --max-batch-size=50` → reflected in config |\n| `TestParseFlags_CustomSearchLimits` | `--max-search-results=200 --max-search-depth=20` → reflected in config |\n\n#### FileManager Tests (`files/manager_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestNewFileManager_Defaults` | Zero config → default limits applied |\n| `TestNewFileManager_CustomConfig` | Custom config → limits reflected |\n| `TestNewFileManager_InvalidWorkspace` | Non-existent workspace → error |\n\n#### Sanitize Tests (`files/sanitize_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestSanitizePath_NormalPath` | `hello.txt` → workspace/hello.txt |\n| `TestSanitizePath_Subdirectory` | `src/main.go` → workspace/src/main.go |\n| `TestSanitizePath_AbsolutePath` | `/etc/passwd` → workspace/etc/passwd |\n| `TestSanitizePath_ParentTraversal` | `../../etc/passwd` → ErrPathTraversal |\n| `TestSanitizePath_SymlinkEscape` | Symlink pointing outside workspace → ErrPathTraversal |\n| `TestSanitizePath_EmptyPath` | `\"\"` → workspace root |\n\n#### ReadFile Tests (`files/read_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestReadFile_EntireFile` | Read full file → Base64 content, total_size, read_bytes |\n| `TestReadFile_WithOffset` | offset=7 → content from offset |\n| `TestReadFile_WithOffsetAndLimit` | offset=7, limit=5 → 5 bytes from offset |\n| `TestReadFile_OffsetExceedsSize` | offset > file size → empty content, read_bytes=0 |\n| `TestReadFile_LimitExceedsRemaining` | limit > remaining bytes → read to EOF |\n| `TestReadFile_NegativeOffset` | offset=-1 → treated as 0 |\n| `TestReadFile_Directory` | path is directory → HTTP 400 |\n| `TestReadFile_NotFound` | path doesn't exist → HTTP 404 |\n| `TestReadFile_PathTraversal` | `../../etc/passwd` → HTTP 400 |\n\n#### WriteFile Tests (`files/write_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestWriteFile_Overwrite` | Replace file content |\n| `TestWriteFile_Append` | Append to existing file |\n| `TestWriteFile_AtOffset` | Write at specific offset without truncation |\n| `TestWriteFile_CreateParent` | `create_parent=true` → directories created |\n| `TestWriteFile_NoCreateParent` | `create_parent=false`, missing parent → error |\n| `TestWriteFile_InvalidBase64` | Invalid base64 → HTTP 400 |\n| `TestWriteFile_ToDirectory` | Path is directory → HTTP 400 |\n\n#### StatFile Tests (`files/stat_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestStatFile_RegularFile` | File metadata returned |\n| `TestStatFile_Directory` | `is_dir: true` |\n| `TestStatFile_Symlink` | `is_symlink: true` |\n| `TestStatFile_NotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n| `TestStatFile_PathTraversal` | HTTP 400 |\n\n#### ListFiles Tests (`files/list_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestListFiles_DirectoryContents` | Returns file entries |\n| `TestListFiles_MissingPath` | HTTP 400 |\n| `TestListFiles_NotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n| `TestListFiles_NotDirectory` | HTTP 400 |\n\n#### Upload Tests (`files/upload_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestUpload_Multipart` | Multipart form upload |\n| `TestUpload_JSONBase64` | JSON body with Base64 content |\n| `TestUpload_ChunkedSingle` | Single chunk (no chunk headers) → direct write |\n| `TestUpload_ChunkedMulti` | 3 chunks → merged correctly |\n| `TestUpload_ChunkedOutOfOrder` | Chunks 2,0,1 → assembled in order 0,1,2 |\n| `TestUpload_ChunkExceedsMax` | Chunk > MaxChunkSize → HTTP 413 |\n| `TestUpload_ChunkCleanup` | After merge, no .chunk.* files remain |\n\n#### Download Tests (`files/download_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestDownload_FullFile` | No Range header → HTTP 200, full content |\n| `TestDownload_RangePartial` | `Range: bytes=0-499` → HTTP 206, Content-Range |\n| `TestDownload_RangeToEOF` | `Range: bytes=500-` → bytes 500 to end |\n| `TestDownload_RangeBeyondSize` | `Range: bytes=200-300` on 100-byte file → HTTP 416 |\n| `TestDownload_Directory` | HTTP 400 |\n| `TestDownload_NotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n\n#### Delete Tests (`files/delete_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestDelete_SingleFile` | Delete one file |\n| `TestDelete_SingleNotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n| `TestDelete_BatchAllSuccess` | Multiple files deleted |\n| `TestDelete_BatchPartialFailure` | Some succeed, some fail → partial results |\n| `TestDelete_BatchExceedsMax` | > MaxBatchSize → HTTP 400 |\n| `TestDelete_NonEmptyDirectory` | HTTP 400 |\n| `TestDelete_EmptyDirectory` | Success |\n\n#### Move Tests (`files/move_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestMove_RenameFile` | Rename within same directory |\n| `TestMove_MoveToSubdirectory` | Move to existing subdirectory |\n| `TestMove_SourceNotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n| `TestMove_DestParentNotFound` | HTTP 400 |\n| `TestMove_EscapeWorkspace` | Destination escapes workspace → HTTP 400 |\n\n#### MkDir Tests (`files/mkdir_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestMkDir_CreateNew` | New directory created, `created: true` |\n| `TestMkDir_AlreadyExists` | Directory exists, `created: false` |\n| `TestMkDir_CustomMode` | Mode 0700 applied |\n| `TestMkDir_PathIsFile` | HTTP 400 |\n\n#### Search Tests (`files/search_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestSearch_FindFiles` | Glob pattern matches files |\n| `TestSearch_RecursiveGlob` | Pattern matches in subdirectories |\n| `TestSearch_Truncated` | Results limited to max_results, `truncated: true` |\n| `TestSearch_NoMatches` | Empty matches, `truncated: false` |\n| `TestSearch_RootNotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n| `TestSearch_RootIsFile` | HTTP 400 |\n| `TestSearch_InvalidPattern` | HTTP 400 |\n| `TestSearch_DepthLimit` | Directories beyond MaxSearchDepth skipped |\n\n#### Chmod Tests (`files/chmod_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestChmod_ChangePermissions` | Mode changed successfully |\n| `TestChmod_InvalidMode` | HTTP 400 |\n| `TestChmod_ModeOutOfRange` | `07777` → HTTP 400 |\n| `TestChmod_NotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n\n#### Server Integration Tests (`server_test.go`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestServer_RoutesRegistered` | All 11 file management routes exist |\n| `TestServer_LegacyRoutesRemoved` | `POST /api/files` → 404/400, `GET /api/files/*` → 404 |\n| `TestServer_HealthCheck` | `/health` returns 200 |\n| `TestServer_AuthRequired` | Requests without JWT → 401 |\n\n### 6.2 Test Helpers\n\n```go\nfunc setupTestWorkspace(t *testing.T) (string, func()) {\n    dir := t.TempDir()\n    return dir, func() {}\n}\n\nfunc createTestFile(t *testing.T, workspace, relPath, content string) string {\n    fullPath := filepath.Join(workspace, relPath)\n    os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(fullPath), 0755)\n    os.WriteFile(fullPath, []byte(content), 0644)\n    return fullPath\n}\n\nfunc newTestServer(t *testing.T, workspace string) *httptest.Server {\n    cfg := Config{\n        Port:      0,\n        Workspace: workspace,\n        FileConfig: FileConfig{\n            MaxChunkSize:     files.DefaultMaxChunkSize,\n            MaxBatchSize:     files.DefaultMaxBatchSize,\n            MaxSearchResults: files.DefaultMaxSearchResults,\n            MaxSearchDepth:   files.DefaultMaxSearchDepth,\n        },\n    }\n    // Note: tests may need to mock JWT auth or use test keys\n    s := NewServer(cfg)\n    return httptest.NewServer(s.engine)\n}\n\nfunc performJSONRequest(method, url string, body interface{}) *http.Response {\n    var buf bytes.Buffer\n    if body != nil {\n        json.NewEncoder(&buf).Encode(body)\n    }\n    req, _ := http.NewRequest(method, url, &buf)\n    req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    // Add JWT token header for auth\n    return http.DefaultClient.Do(req)\n}\n```\n\n### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n\n- **Filesystem:** Use `t.TempDir()` for isolated test workspaces\n- **JWT Auth:** Generate test RSA key pairs for signing/verification\n- **Chunked Upload:** Write test chunks directly to temp directory, verify merge\n- **Symlink Tests:** Create symlinks within test workspace pointing to known targets\n\n### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `go build ./pkg/picod/...` compiles\n2. `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` produces no warnings\n3. `go test ./pkg/picod/... -v` all pass\n4. `go test -race ./pkg/picod/...` no data race warnings\n5. `go mod tidy` results in no changes\n6. All new handlers have unit tests covering normal, error, and edge cases\n7. Legacy AR-015 tests continue to pass (upload, list, download, sanitize)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Deployment Considerations\n\n1. **Workspace Jail:** The workspace directory must be an absolute path. Symlinks in the workspace path are resolved at startup. All file operations are constrained within the resolved workspace.\n\n2. **Chunked Upload Temp Directory:** Temporary chunk files are stored in `<os.TempDir>/picod-chunks/`. Ensure sufficient disk space for concurrent chunked uploads. Temp files are cleaned up after merge or on error.\n\n3. **MaxChunkSize:** Default 32 MiB. For large file transfers, clients should split into smaller chunks. The server validates each chunk size independently.\n\n4. **MaxBatchSize:** Default 100. Batch delete operations continue on individual failures and report partial results. No atomicity guarantee across batch entries.\n\n5. **Search Depth Limit:** Default 50 levels. Prevents stack overflow or excessive traversal on deeply nested directory structures.\n\n6. **File Mode Validation:** Mode strings are parsed as octal (base 8). Maximum valid mode is 0777. Modes exceeding this are rejected.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Implementation Steps\n\n### Phase 1: Subpackage Scaffolding (Day 1)\n\n1. Create `pkg/picod/files/` directory structure\n2. Define `FileManager` interface in `manager.go`\n3. Migrate `sanitizePath` to `files/sanitize.go`\n4. Move request/response types to `files/types.go`\n5. Write `sanitize_test.go` (migrate from existing tests)\n\n### Phase 2: Core File Operations (Day 2)\n\n1. Implement `ReadFile` in `read.go` + tests\n2. Implement `WriteFile` in `write.go` + tests\n3. Implement `StatFile` in `stat.go` + tests\n4. Migrate `ListFiles` to `list.go` + tests\n5. Update `Config` struct with file management fields\n\n### Phase 3: Upload/Download with Advanced Features (Day 3)\n\n1. Migrate `UploadFile` to `upload.go` with chunk support + tests\n2. Migrate `DownloadFile` to `download.go` with Range support + tests\n3. Implement `DeleteFile` in `delete.go` with batch support + tests\n4. Implement `MoveFile` in `move.go` + tests\n\n### Phase 4: Utility Operations (Day 4)\n\n1. Implement `MkDir` in `mkdir.go` + tests\n2. Implement `SearchFiles` in `search.go` + tests\n3. Implement `Chmod` in `chmod.go` + tests\n4. Update `server.go` route registration\n5. Update `config.go` with CLI flags\n\n### Phase 5: Integration & Gate (Day 5)\n\n1. Run `go build ./pkg/picod/...`\n2. Run `go vet ./pkg/picod/...`\n3. Run `go test ./pkg/picod/... -v`\n4. Run `go test -race ./pkg/picod/...`\n5. Run `go mod tidy`\n6. Verify legacy AR-015 tests pass\n7. Remove old `files.go`\n\n---\n\n## 9. Future Changes\n\n| Change | Description | Priority |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| AR-0XX | File watch/tail API for real-time content streaming | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Archive download (tar/zip) for directory downloads | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | File copy/duplicate API | P3 |\n| AR-0XX | Recursive directory delete (`os.RemoveAll`) with safety guard | P3 |\n| AR-0XX | File content diff API | P3 |\n\n### Known Limitations\n\n- Batch delete is not atomic; partial failures are reported but not rolled back\n- Chunked uploads require all chunks to arrive; no resume support for interrupted uploads\n- Search uses `filepath.WalkDir` which is synchronous; large directories may block the handler\n- No file locking; concurrent writes to the same file may cause data corruption\n- Symlink following is limited to the final path resolution; intermediate symlinks within the workspace are followed\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime.go\">\nERROR [51:25] undefined: LabelSessionID\nERROR [77:29] undefined: LabelSandboxName\nERROR [78:29] undefined: LabelWorkloadName\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchm